Transcript: Ọ bụ mụoni bụ Pọl, onyeozi nke Onyenwoayị, eehigi na ẹka madụ ma ọ bụgụ ụmụ madụ, kama nke hiteri na ẹka Onyenwoayị Jisọs Karaịs yaa Chineke bụ Nna, onye meri e ya o hi na ọnwụ pavuru,
English Translation: Paul, an apostle—sent not from men nor by a man, but by Jesus Christ and God the Father, who raised him from the dead—

Transcript: mụa ụmụne m na ohu na ime Karaịs mụa wo nọ, na-edejeri, Nde chọchị na ohu nọ na Galeshia ẹkwụkwọa.
English Translation: and all the brothers and sisters with me, To the churches in Galatia:

Transcript: Ekpere m bụ na ẹwụọma yaa udo nke Onyenwoayị Jisọs Karaịs yaa Chineke Nnade aayị dịrị unu,
English Translation: Grace and peace to you from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ,

Transcript: na Karaịs onye jiri onwoe chụa ẹja maka ihe ọjọọ aayị ma a nafụta ayị na ihe ọjọọ nke ọgbọ a dịka nke ọ bụ ọchụchọ Chineke Nnade aayị,
English Translation: who gave himself for our sins to rescue us from the present evil age, according to the will of our God and Father,

Transcript: onye yaanịa nwo otuto oohu tututu rue mgbe agwụ-agwụ. Amịn.
English Translation: to whom be glory for ever and ever. Amen.

Transcript: O juru m ẹnya na ọ tọgụ ike unu habuwokozuri Onyem kubeteri unu hite na ẹwụọma Karaịs garị na-agbasozukwekwe oziọma ọzọ.
English Translation: I am astonished that you are so quickly deserting the one who called you to live in the grace of Christ and are turning to a different gospel—

Transcript: Ọ dịkwanụgụ oziọma ọzọ ọ bụ, kama a hụrụ m na o nworu nde bịarị bịa na-etihechi unu ihu, na-agbanwo eziokwu nke oziọma bayeri Karaịs.
English Translation: which is really no gospel at all. Evidently some people are throwing you into confusion and are trying to pervert the gospel of Christ.

Transcript: Ekpere m bụ na Chineke taa onye ọọbụla ahụhụ bịarị bịa na-ezi oziọma ọzọ dị iche na ọnwanịa ayị ziri, ma ọ bụgụ ayịa madụ, ma ọ bụgụ maaozi hi na elugwe, na ntaramahụhụ a dịị rue mgbe agwụ-agwụ.
English Translation: But even if we or an angel from heaven should preach a gospel other than the one we preached to you, let them be under God’s curse!

Transcript: Dịka nke ayị hiworu kwue, ana m ekwukwekwe e ọzọ: Onye ọọbụla je-abịa bịa na-ezi unu oziọma ọzọ dị iche na ọmụanịm unu nabatarị na mbụ, na ntaram-ahụhụ a agwụkwa agwụ.
English Translation: As we have already said, so now I say again: If anybody is preaching to you a gospel other than what you accepted, let them be under God’s curse!

Transcript: Ẹɦụọdị, m na-achọzu imete obu nde madụ sa ọ ka ọ bụm ihe dị Chineke ma bụ ihe m na-achọ? Ya ọ bụrụ na ana m achọ na mụ emete obu nde madụ bụnụ ahịaga na abụgụ m onyeozi Karaịs.
English Translation: Am I now trying to win the approval of human beings, or of God? Or am I trying to please people? If I were still trying to please people, I would not be a servant of Christ.

Transcript: Achọrụ m na unu mata ụmụnna, na ọ bụdịgị madụ duyeri m bịa bịa-ezije oziọma madụ meteri.
English Translation: I want you to know, brothers and sisters, that the gospel I preached is not of human origin.

Transcript: Ọ dịgị madụ ọọbụla m natarị ozi e na ẹka, bụgụ madụ ziri mu e, kama ọ bụ Jisọs Karaịs yaẹkaa kpuheeri mu e.
English Translation: I did not receive it from any man, nor was I taught it; rather, I received it by revelation from Jesus Christ.

Transcript: Unu hiwokokwenuru nụ otue madụ m bụwaarị na ndụ m nọrụ na-ebu na okpukpe nde Juu. Nke m garị na-akpagbu nde otu nzuko nke Chineke, na-achọ ịla a na iyi.
English Translation: For you have heard of my previous way of life in Judaism, how intensely I persecuted the church of God and tried to destroy it.

Transcript: A nọrụ m na-agba mbọ na ozi okpukpe nde Juu karịa ntụtụ madụ mụa wo bụ ẹlịa, na-ebu isi kpụlịkpụlị na ihe bayeri idebe omenalị nde nnadoche ayị wo na ohu.
English Translation: I was advancing in Judaism beyond many of my own age among my people and was extremely zealous for the traditions of my fathers.

Transcript: Ọbụ na o ruru mgbe Chineke Onye hiri na ẹhọ neewo kewefute m, hite na ẹwụọma a, ya o ku m maka na o heri e,
English Translation: But when God, who set me apart from my mother’s womb and called me by his grace, was pleased

Transcript: ya o kpuheeri m, gusi m Onye ọkpara a bụ, na mụ enwo ike izise oziọma bayeri e na alị nde aabụgụ nde Juu, ka ọọdị madụ ọọbụla m jeri je-akụta isi.
English Translation: to reveal his Son in me so that I might preach him among the Gentiles, my immediate response was not to consult any human being.

Transcript: Ọ dịkọkwanụgụ mgbe m nyikogeeri na Jerusalẹm ije je-ahụ ndem buru m ụzọ bụrụ ndeozi Karaịs, kama agaarị m jege alị Arabịa, nọtụ m lahachichee na Damaskọs.
English Translation: I did not go up to Jerusalem to see those who were apostles before I was, but I went into Arabia. Later I returned to Damascus.

Transcript: Ọ bụrụrị mgbe ahọ ẹtọ gadụụrụ ta m garị jege Jerusalẹm kpakwuru Pita, mụa ya je anọa abalị irile ise.
English Translation: Then after three years, I went up to Jerusalem to get acquainted with Peter and stayed with him fifteen days.

Transcript: Onyeozi Karaịs ọzọkwam m jekwuru bụrụ Jems bụ nwane nwoke Onyenwoayị.
English Translation: I saw none of the other apostles—only James, the Lord’s brother.

Transcript: Chineke bụ onye m guzo na ihu e maarị na ihe m na-ederi unu na ẹkwụkwọ a bụ eziokwu, na agagị m ụga.
English Translation: I assure you before God that what I am writing you is no lie.

Transcript: Emedue, m garị na-eje ọnụmara Siria yaa Silisia.
English Translation: Then I went to Syria and Cilicia.

Transcript: Nde chọchịga na ohu nọrụ na Judia nọ na ime Karaịs adịdịgị ma ọ bụgụ onye aanị na ime wo maarị onye m bụ.
English Translation: I was personally unknown to the churches of Judea that are in Christ.

Transcript: Ihe wo maarịm bụ na nde madụ nọrụ na-asị, “Nwoke m nọrụ na-akpagbu nde otu nzuko nke Onyenwoayị na-ezisezukwe oziọma nke okwukwem na Karaịs ọ nọrụ na-achọ nke ọ je-ọga kpochefuu.”
English Translation: They only heard the report: “The man who formerly persecuted us is now preaching the faith he once tried to destroy.”

Transcript: Wo toe Chineke otuto hiri ne maka m.
English Translation: And they praised God because of me.

Transcript: Mgbe ahọ irile ẹnọ gadụụrụ, m garị jegechee Jerusalẹm mụa Banabas, Taịtus sokoru ayị je.
English Translation: Then after fourteen years, I went up again to Jerusalem, this time with Barnabas. I took Titus along also.

Transcript: Ejeri m ya njem mu maka na Chineke kpuheeri mu e. M jege je-atụsaarị wo oziọmam m nọrụ na-ezige nde aabụgụ nde Juu. Mụa nde bụrụ ahịaga ọkpọtọkpọ oke nde isi nke nzuko nke Onyenwoayị hụtakọdụa ihu la ihu, na mụ emedukwee bụrụ onye gbarị ọsọ na amaka.
English Translation: I went in response to a revelation and, meeting privately with those esteemed as leaders, I presented to them the gospel that I preach among the Gentiles. I wanted to be sure I was not running and had not been running my race in vain.

Transcript: Ọ dịdịgị mgbe a sịrị na Taịtus mụa ya yịrị bụrụ onye Giriki, aabụdịgị onye Juu je-esie ọnutu e ẹɦụm nde Juu na-eme na omenalị Chineke nịrị wo.
English Translation: Yet not even Titus, who was with me, was compelled to be circumcised, even though he was a Greek.

Transcript: A paliteri ụka bayeri osise ọnutu na mgbe nde ụmụnna ụfọdị aabụgụ nde ezibe ụmụnna, gaarị bịa na-enyovu onwunworu onwonye ayị debeeri onwaayị na ime Karaịs Jisọs, na-achọ na wo debe ayị nde ohu.
English Translation: This matter arose because some false believers had infiltrated our ranks to spy on the freedom we have in Christ Jesus and to make us slaves.

Transcript: Ayị ekweyediirigi wo ma ọ hagịnwa tịkọọ maka na ayị chọrụ na eziokwu nke oziọma a ruru unu ẹka, fụtarị unu ihe.
English Translation: We did not give in to them for a moment, so that the truth of the gospel might be preserved for you.

Transcript: Nde dịka ọ bụ wo sofuteri isi karịdụa na ya ozi e adịgị ihe wo fụtaarị m, maka na Chineke ekpegi ikpe na nke ihe dị na ẹnya madụ. Ya ndem adịgị ihe wo yekoru na ozi m.
English Translation: As for those who were held in high esteem—whatever they were makes no difference to me; God does not show favoritism—they added nothing to my message.

Transcript: Ọbụ na wo medueri chọfụta na eziri m ozi e je ezie nde aabụgụ nde Juu oziọma, na ọ bụkọkwanụ ya Chineke aanịm zikoru Pita ozie je ezie nde Juu.
English Translation: On the contrary, they recognized that I had been entrusted with the task of preaching the gospel to the uncircumcised, just as Peter had been to the circumcised.

Transcript: Na ya Chineke m ziri Pita jekwuru nde Juu dịka onyeozi Karaịs, bụ a zikoru m jekwu nde aabụgụ nde Juu dịka onyeozi Karaịs.
English Translation: For God, who was at work in Peter as an apostle to the circumcised, was also at work in me as an apostle to the Gentiles.

Transcript: Jems yaa Pita maa Jọn bụrụ ahịaga nde bụ isi-sekpu-ntị na ime nzuko nke Onyenwoayị medueri chọfụta na Chineke nworu ihe o yeri m na ẹka, wo nabata mụa Banabas, ayịa wo yịrị na-arụ ọrụ. Wo jayecheeri ayị ayị zije nde aabụgụ nde Juu oziọma na woande zije nde Juu oziọma wo.
English Translation: James, Peter and John, those esteemed as pillars, gave me and Barnabas the right hand of fellowship when they recognized the grace given to me. They agreed that we should go to the Gentiles, and they to the circumcised.

Transcript: Ihe wo jayecheeri ayị bụ ayị rịtaje nde ọdịgị nke ọha wo na ozi aayị, bụkọkwanụ ihe nọrụ na-adị m na obu mgbe ọọbụla na mụ emeje.
English Translation: All they asked was that we should continue to remember the poor, the very thing I had been eager to do all along.

Transcript: Mgbe Pita bịarị na Antịọk, m guzogidie ihu la ihu maka otue ẹgwa ọ kparị eekwesidigi ekwesi.
English Translation: When Peter came to Antioch, I opposed him to his face, because he stood condemned.

Transcript: O hiri na-amayekote ẹka na ụsarị nri yaa nde aabụgụ nde Juu na-esoko ụzọ Onyenwoayị ma a na-eri nri. Ya o rue mgbe nde Juu nde Jems duyeri ozi bịarị, Pita kwobezu ụjọ ihe ya ndem ka ekweyeri na osise ọnutu je-asị, ka ookwesi amayekote ẹka na ụsarị nri yaa nde aabụgụ nde Juu.
English Translation: For before certain men came from James, he used to eat with the Gentiles. But when they arrived, he began to draw back and separate himself from the Gentiles because he was afraid of those who belonged to the circumcision group.

Transcript: Pita yaa nde Juu ọzọmga na-egwuchi gwuchizu onwowo nke na wo ratakọzuru Banabas ya o so wo na ya ndụ mma ihu ẹbọọm.
English Translation: The other Jews joined him in his hypocrisy, so that by their hypocrisy even Barnabas was led astray.

Transcript: Mgbe m hụrụ ihe nọrụ na-agba, na wo anọsịdịgị na-eme ihe eziokwu nke oziọma ziri, m chịrị a wụhakọarịm Pita ihu la ihu na ihu madụ oohu sị a, “Pita, ị bụ onye Juu, ọbụ na i na-ibuzu ndụ gụ ka onye aabụgụ onye Juu. Ndakwanụa nke ị garị na-achọ na i kwogide nde aabụgụ nde Juu na wo debeje omenalị nde Juu?”
English Translation: When I saw that they were not acting in line with the truth of the gospel, I said to Peter in front of them all, “You are a Jew, yet you live like a Gentile and not like a Jew. How is it, then, that you force Gentiles to follow Jewish customs?

Transcript: “Ayịande bụ amụrụ amụ alị Juu aabụgụ nde mba ọzọ bụ ‘nde ihe ọjọọ’,
English Translation: “We who are Jews by birth and not sinful Gentiles

Transcript: maarị na ọ dịgị onye a na-anabata na ihu Chineke maka na ike dị a debetue iwu oohu nke Chineke nịrị Mosisi, kama na ọ bụ hite na onwunwo okwukwe na Jisọs Karaịs. Ayịandekọ na-enwo okwukwe na Karaịs Jisọs ma ayị bụrụ nde a nabatarị na ihu Chineke, ka ọọbụ na-edebeturu iwum Chineke nịrị Mosisi, maka na ọ dịgị onye a je-anabata na ihu Chineke hite na edebe iwum Chineke nịrị Mosisi.
English Translation: know that a person is not justified by the works of the law, but by faith in Jesus Christ. So we, too, have put our faith in Christ Jesus that we may be justified by faith in Christ and not by the works of the law, because by the works of the law no one will be justified.

Transcript: “Ibe ayịande na-achọ na ayị bụrụ nde a nabatarị na ihu Chineke hite na ẹka Karaịs chọfụtakọrụ na ayị bụ nde ihe ọjọọ, ọ bụ ahịaga na ọ bụ Karaịs na-akwagide ihe ọjọọ? Tụfịakwa, ọ dịgị ya ẹɦụm!
English Translation: “But if, in seeking to be justified in Christ, we Jews find ourselves also among the sinners, doesn’t that mean that Christ promotes sin? Absolutely not!

Transcript: M bịa-ebidokwekwe na isi na-apaliteche ụzọ ochiem m kutuworu na ọ dịgị ma, e gusiri m na-abụkọ m onye na-emebi iwu.
English Translation: If I rebuild what I destroyed, then I really would be a lawbreaker.

Transcript: Ya ọ bụrụ ihe gbasịrị iwu, adị m ka onye nwụhụrụ anwụhụ na ibe iwu dị ma m nworu ike dịrị Chineke ndụ.
English Translation: “For through the law I died to the law so that I might live for God.

Transcript: Maka na a kpọgbukotewo mụa Karaịs na elu obe, ọ bụsịgị mụoni nọ ndụ a, kama ọ bụzu Karaịs dị ndụ na ime m. Ndụ m dị na anụhụ, adị mụ a hite na ntụkwasịobu m nworu na ibe Ọkpara Chineke nọ, onye hụrụ m na ẹnya weri onwoe chụa ẹja na isi m.
English Translation: I have been crucified with Christ and I no longer live, but Christ lives in me. The life I now live in the body, I live by faith in the Son of God, who loved me and gave himself for me.

Transcript: Esogu m ndem na-eme ẹwụọma Chineke ka a sị na ọ dịgị ihe ọ fụtarị, maka na ya ọ bụrụ na madụ nworu ike ịbụ onye ụmara-ọma Chineke hite na edebe iwu bụ ahịaga na Karaịs nwụhụrụ na amaka, na ọnwụ a adịgị uru ọ barị.”
English Translation: I do not set aside the grace of God, for if righteousness could be gained through the law, Christ died for nothing!

Transcript: Unuande Galeshia nde iberibe! Onye riri unu amosu? E meri e ya o dochee unu ẹnya nke Jisọs Karaịs garị nwụhụ na elu obe.
English Translation: You foolish Galatians! Who has bewitched you? Before your very eyes Jesus Christ was clearly portrayed as crucified.

Transcript: Unu kakweleri m ihe aanị a: Chineke ọ nịrị unu Maa Nsọ a maka na nke unu garị debe iwu e na ohu saa ọ bụ maka na unu nụrụ oziọma bayeri Karaịs, unu kweye na ya?
English Translation: I would like to learn just one thing from you: Did you receive the Spirit by the works of the law, or by believing what you heard?

Transcript: Unu bụchaam nde iberibe ya ẹɦụm? Ọ bụ unua Maa Nsọ yịkọdụa na unu ana-achọkwakwa na unu weri ikike madụ amaka na-achọ ezumoke uunu?
English Translation: Are you so foolish? After beginning by means of the Spirit, are you now trying to finish by means of the flesh?

Transcript: Unu ririm ahụhụ a na ohu na amaka? A manụụrụ m na ọ bụgụ na amaka!
English Translation: Have you experienced so much in vain—if it really was in vain?

Transcript: Chineke ọ nịrị unu Maa Nsọ a, na-arụ ọrụ ahụma a na ohu maka na unu na-edebe iwu na ohu, saa ọ bụ maka na unu kweyeri na oziọma unu nụrụ?
English Translation: So again I ask, does God give you his Spirit and work miracles among you by the works of the law, or by your believing what you heard?

Transcript: Unu letekwele onye dịka Eburaham, “Onye kweyeri na Chineke, a gụyeri e ye na onye meri ụmara-ọma.”
English Translation: So also Abraham “believed God, and it was credited to him as righteousness.”

Transcript: Ẹɦụọdị, unu gọta na ndem na ohu nworu okwukwe bụ nde bụ ụmụ Eburaham.
English Translation: Understand, then, that those who have faith are children of Abraham.

Transcript: Ẹkwụkwọ Nsọ gbarị ama sị na Chineke je-anabata nde aabụgụ nde Juu maka okwukwe wo je-enwo na ibe Chineke nọ. A gbaarị a Eburaham ama na oziọma sị a, “Mba na ohu je-agata ẹka gị nata ngọzi Chineke.”
English Translation: Scripture foresaw that God would justify the Gentiles by faith, and announced the gospel in advance to Abraham: “All nations will be blessed through you.”

Transcript: Ndem na ohu nworu okwukwe na ibe Karaịs nọ je-esoko Eburaham nata ngọzi na ẹka Chineke maka okwukwe Eburaham.
English Translation: So those who rely on faith are blessed along with Abraham, the man of faith.

Transcript: Ndem na ohu na-achọ omume ihe dị Chineke ma hite na edebe iwu na ohu Chineke nịrị Mosisi nọ na okpuru avụm ọnụ, maka na e deri e na Ẹkwụkwọ Nsọ sị, “Onye ọọbụla eemetetugu ihom na ohu e deri na ẹkwụkwọ iwu bụ onye a vụrụ ọnụ.”
English Translation: For all who rely on the works of the law are under a curse, as it is written: “Cursed is everyone who does not continue to do everything written in the Book of the Law.”

Transcript: O doru ẹnya na ọ dịgị onye je-abụ onye a nabatarị na ihu Chineke hite na edebe iwu, maka na, “Nde ụmara-ọma je-eji okwukwe na-ebu ndụ wo.”
English Translation: Clearly no one who relies on the law is justified before God, because “the righteous will live by faith.”

Transcript: Edebe iwu ehibegi isi na onwunwo okwukwe, kama, “Onye ọọbụla chọrụ iji edebe iwu na-ebu ndụ a je-edebeturiri ihom na ohu e deri na iwu.”
English Translation: The law is not based on faith; on the contrary, it says, “The person who does these things will live by them.”

Transcript: Karaịs gbafụtarị ayị na avụm ọnụ nke iwu maka na o jiri onwoe mieri ayị onye a vụrụ ọnụ ẹɦụm ọ nwụhụrụ na elu obe, dịka nke Ẹkwụkwọ Nsọ kwuru, “Onye ọọbụla a kpọgburu na elu osisi bụ onye Chineke vụrụ ọnụ.”
English Translation: Christ redeemed us from the curse of the law by becoming a curse for us, for it is written: “Cursed is everyone who is hung on a pole.”

Transcript: Ọ gbafụtarị ayị na okpuru avụm ọnụ ma ayị natakọ ngọzi a nịrị Eburaham, ma ọ ga ẹka Jisọs Karaịs rubeko nde aabụgụ nde Juu, ma ayị jiri okwukwe nata nkwa Chineke kweri ịnị ayị Maa Nsọ a.
English Translation: He redeemed us in order that the blessing given to Abraham might come to the Gentiles through Christ Jesus, so that by faith we might receive the promise of the Spirit.

Transcript: Ọ bụ m Pọl, nwaọrụ Karaịs Jisọs, onye Chineke kuru ịbụ onyeozi Karaịs a họtarị izise oziọma bayeri Chineke na-ederi unu ẹkwụkwọa.
English Translation: Paul, a servant of Christ Jesus, called to be an apostle and set apart for the gospel of God—

Transcript: Oziọma Chineke jiri nde amụma a kwe nkwa ẹkamgbe dịka nke e deri e na Ẹkwụkwọ Nsọ,
English Translation: the gospel he promised beforehand through his prophets in the Holy Scriptures

Transcript: ihe bayeri Ọkpara a, onye bịarị na ụwa dịka madụ hite na eriri Devidi.
English Translation: regarding his Son, who as to his earthly life was a descendant of David,

Transcript: Chineke gusiri na ọ bụ Ọkpara a hite na omumie na o hi na ọnwụ pavuru na ike nke Maa Nsọ: Jisọs Karaịs Onyenwoayị.
English Translation: and who through the Spirit of holiness was appointed the Son of God in power by his resurrection from the dead: Jesus Christ our Lord.

Transcript: Chineke kwobe Jisọs Karaịs gusi ayị ẹwụọma a, me ayị bụrụ ndeozi Karaịs je-ekufute ntụtụ madụ na etiti nde aabụgụ nde Juu, na wo sokoru ru beri Chineke isi, nwoe ntụkwasịobu maka ẹha a.
English Translation: Through him we received grace and apostleship to call all the Gentiles to the obedience that comes from faith for his name’s sake.

Transcript: Unuande Rom sokozu na ya ndem Chineke kuru na unu bụkọzuru ndeke Jisọs Karaịs.
English Translation: And you also are among those Gentiles who are called to belong to Jesus Christ.

Transcript: Ana m ederi unu oohu nde bu na Rom ẹkwụkwọa, bụ nde Chineke hụrụ na ẹnya, ku wo, ịbụ ndekie dị nsọ. Na udo yaa ẹwụọma Chineke bụ Nnade aayị yaa nke Jisọs Karaịs bụ Onyenwoayị dịrị unu.
English Translation: To all in Rome who are loved by God and called to be his holy people: Grace and peace to you from God our Father and from the Lord Jesus Christ.

Transcript: Nke mbụ, aga m ẹka Jisọs Karaịs na-ekele Chineke m na isi uunu, maka a na-akpa ihe bayeri okwukwe uunu na ụwa na ohu.
English Translation: First, I thank my God through Jesus Christ for all of you, because your faith is being reported all over the world.

Transcript: Chineke, Onye m ji obu m na ohu na-ejeri ezise oziọma bayeri Ọkpara a, bụ onye ẹkebe m na ana m arịta unu
English Translation: God, whom I serve in my spirit in preaching the gospel of his Son, is my witness how constantly I remember you

Transcript: mgbe ọọbụla na ekpere. Ana m egororu Chineke ya ọ bụrụ na ọ chọrụ a, na o meheeri m ụzọ na mụ eenwo ike ịkpakwute unu.
English Translation: in my prayers at all times; and I pray that now at last by God’s will the way may be opened for me to come to you.

Transcript: Ọ na-ọgụ m ẹgụ ọkam ịhụ unu, ma m nwo ike weteri unu ụfọdị ihe ọnịnị nke ime maa, ma unu guzosie ike.
English Translation: I long to see you so that I may impart to you some spiritual gift to make you strong—

Transcript: Ọ bụ ahịaga ma ayị gbatarị onwaayị ume na okwukwe ayị nwo.
English Translation: that is, that you and I may be mutually encouraged by each other’s faith.

Transcript: Achọgụ m na unu amakwa, ụmụnna, na ọ dịwo akpa ntụtụ ẹkamgbe m hịhịadụrụ ma m bịa nke uunu. Ọbụ na o nwom ihe na-egbochu mụ eni tututu rute ẹɦụọdị. Obu m bụ ma m nwo ike kuteri Jisọs nde na-eso ụzọ a na etiti uunu ẹɦụm m nwoteduworu na mba ọzọga nde aabụgụ nde Juu.
English Translation: I do not want you to be unaware, brothers and sisters, that I planned many times to come to you (but have been prevented from doing so until now) in order that I might have a harvest among you, just as I have had among the other Gentiles.

Transcript: Eji m mba oohu ụgwọ, maa nde bụ nde Giriki maa nde aabụgụ, maa nde maarị ihe maa nde aadịgị nke wo maarị.
English Translation: I am obligated both to Greeks and non-Greeks, both to the wise and the foolish.

Transcript: Ọ bụ a meri ọ na-ọgụsi m ẹgụ ike iziko unuande nọ na Rom oziọma.
English Translation: That is why I am so eager to preach the gospel also to you who are in Rome.

Transcript: Izi oziọma adịgị m egwu, maka na ọ bụ a bụ ikike Chineke ji na-azọfụta ụmụ madụ, nde kwerini: hitehee na nde Juu ta na o rubeje nde aabụgụ nde Juu.
English Translation: For I am not ashamed of the gospel, because it is the power of God that brings salvation to everyone who believes: first to the Jew, then to the Gentile.

Transcript: Maka na ọ bụ na ime ya oziọ￾maa bụ ibe e kpuheri ụmara-ọma nke Chineke. Ọ dabeeri hite na isi rue na ọgwụgwụ na onwunwo okwukwe. Dịka nke e deri e na Ẹkwụkwọ Nsọ, “Nde ụmara-ọma je-adị ndụ hite na okwukwe wo.”
English Translation: For in the gospel the righteousness of God is revealed—a righteousness that is by faith from first to last, just as it is written: “The righteous will live by faith.”

Transcript: E hiwo na elugwe gusi iwe-ọkụ Chineke na ibe ụmụ madụ nọ, maka ihe ọjọọ wo yaa arụrụalị wo na-arụ, eekwegi na ya eziokwum bayeri Chineke fụta ihe.
English Translation: The wrath of God is being revealed from heaven against all the godlessness and wickedness of people, who suppress the truth by their wickedness,

Transcript: Iwe-ọkụ Chineke na adakwasị wo maka na o gusituwo wo ihe ọọbụla wo kwesiri ịma bayeri Chineke.
English Translation: since what may be known about God is plain to them, because God has made it plain to them.

Transcript: Hiteri na ẹkamgbe okike ụwa, ikikie aagwụgụ agwụ yaa ihom na ohu o jiri bụrụ Chineke, madụ eenwogu ike ịhụ ẹnya, Chineke emewo ahụtatuem nke wo dị. E nwo ike ịgọta wo hite na ihe oohu o keri eke, nke na madụ adịgị ihe o ji je-agọ ẹgụgọ na ihu Chineke.
English Translation: For since the creation of the world God’s invisible qualities—his eternal power and divine nature—have been clearly seen, being understood from what has been made, so that people are without excuse.

Transcript: Na mgbe wo madụụrụm na ọ bụ a bụ Chineke, ka wo aasọfụrụ a ka Chineke, nịgị a otuto yaa ekele ruturu eni, kama ọrịrị wo bụrụ ihe amaka, obu iberibe wo techuhudue.
English Translation: For although they knew God, they neither glorified him as God nor gave thanks to him, but their thinking became futile and their foolish hearts were darkened.

Transcript: Wo na-asị na wo bụ nde maarị ihe, ọbụ na wo bụ nde iberibe.
English Translation: Although they claimed to be wise, they became fools

Transcript: Kama wo je na-ekperi Chineke onye ebube aanwụhụgụ anwụhụ, wo je-apịtadụa ihe wo pịrị na oyiye madụ amaka na-anwụhụ anwụhụ, ma ọ bụgụ na ụdịdị nnụnụ, ma ọ bụgụ na ụdịdị anụ kwụ ọkpa, ma ọ bụgụ na ụdịdị ihe na-arịga arị, debe na-ekperi.
English Translation: and exchanged the glory of the immortal God for images made to look like a mortal human being and birds and animals and reptiles.

Transcript: Ọ bụ a meri Chineke wefuuru wo ẹka wo je-emeje nke dị wo ma. Wo wụjube na-eme ihe rụrụ arụ wo kpụtarị na obu wo. Wo na enwo mmeko nwoke yaa nwanyị aalụtaarịgị onwowo.
English Translation: Therefore God gave them over in the sinful desires of their hearts to sexual impurity for the degrading of their bodies with one another.

Transcript: Wo tụgarịa eziokwu ihe oohu bayeri Chineke weri ụga bube ụzọ, je na-akpọrụ ihe e keri eke isi na alị, na-ejeri e ozi ta hasịa Onyem keri ihe ọọbụla. Onye yaanịa nwo otuto na ohu rue mgbe agwụ-agwụ. Amịn.
English Translation: They exchanged the truth about God for a lie, and worshiped and served created things rather than the Creator—who is forever praised. Amen.

Transcript: Maka na wo meri ya ẹɦụm, Chineke habue wo wo dasiri na￾eme ihe mmechu-ihu na-agụ wo ẹgụ na omume. Maa nde ụmụ nwanyị wo agbanwokoduwo mmekorite na nke o kwesiri ịdị, na-emezu nke aabụgụ anị.
English Translation: Because of this, God gave them over to shameful lusts. Even their women exchanged natural sexual relations for unnatural ones.

Transcript: Nde nwokeko habuzue inwo mmeko nwoke yaa nwanyị nke Chineke deberi e, na-achọzu nwoke ibe wo. Na nwoke yaa nwoke ibie ana-enwo mmeko ana-asọ egwu. Ọ bụ a meri wo na-anata ntaram-ahụhụ kwesiri woni maka omume ihe rụrụ arụ dịga ya ẹɦụm.
English Translation: In the same way the men also abandoned natural relations with women and were inflamed with lust for one another. Men committed shameful acts with other men, and received in themselves the due penalty for their error.

Transcript: Ọzọ bụ na maka na wo jụkarị ịmata ihe wo kwesiri ịma bayeri Chineke, Chineke habue wo wo na-akpụta ihe rụrụ arụ na obu wo gbagọrụ agbagọ na-eme. Na-eme ihe eekwesigi ekwesi na wo meri.
English Translation: Furthermore, just as they did not think it worthwhile to retain the knowledge of God, so God gave them over to a depraved mind, so that they do what ought not to be done.

Transcript: Ụrụ alị dị iche iche ejuwo wo obu; ihe ọjọọ, ẹnya-ukwu yaa ndụ ọjọọ. Wo bụrụ nde ẹnyụhụ, nde na egbu madụ, nde na-akpa oke, nde ụgọrọ, na-evuru madụ ibe wo ihe na obu, nde na-akpa asịrị,
English Translation: They have become filled with every kind of wickedness, evil, greed and depravity. They are full of envy, murder, strife, deceit and malice. They are gossips,

Transcript: nde na-ekwuto madụ ibe wo, nde ihe Chineke aadịgị ma, nde na-akparị madụ, nde mpako yaa ọtamba, nde na-arịfụta nke a ga na-arụ alị na-efu eze elu, nde na-enufuru nde mụrụ wo isi,
English Translation: slanderers, God-haters, insolent, arrogant and boastful; they invent ways of doing evil; they disobey their parents;

Transcript: nde amamihe kọrụ, eekwesigi na a tụkwasị wo obu, nde obu-ọjọọ, nde dị ụrụ aahatagị a ahata.
English Translation: they have no understanding, no fidelity, no love, no mercy.

Transcript: Wo amakọduworu ntụziẹka ọma nke Chineke, na ọnwụ na-eche nde na-eme ihe dị ya ẹɦụm, wo gaam na ihu na-eme ihe wo na-eme. Ka ọ bụnwa na wo na-emie kama wo na-akwagideko nde na-eme ihe dịga ya ẹɦụm.
English Translation: Although they know God’s righteous decree that those who do such things deserve death, they not only continue to do these very things but also approve of those who practice them.

Transcript: Ọ bụ m Pọl, onyeozi Karaịs Jisọs hite na ọchụchọ Chineke. Ẹkwụkwọ m na-edejeri ụmụ Chineke nọ na Efesọs, bụ nde kwesiri ntụkwasịobu na iso Karaịs Jisọs.
English Translation: Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the will of God, To God’s holy people in Ephesus,[a] the faithful in Christ Jesus:

Transcript: Na ẹwụọma yaa udo Chineke Nnade aayị yaa Onyenwoayị Jisọs Karaịs dịrị unu.
English Translation: Grace and peace to you from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.

Transcript: Na otuto dịrị Chineke bụ Nna nke Onyenwoayị Jisọs Karaịs, Onye gaworu ẹka Karaịs weteri ayị ngọzi nke ime maa na ohu hi na elugwe.
English Translation: Praise be to the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who has blessed us in the heavenly realms with every spiritual blessing in Christ.

Transcript: Ọ bụ Chineke họfụtarị ayị na mgbe aaka ekeheegi ụwa, na ayị bụrụ nde je-adị nsọ, eenwogu nkọjọ ọọbụla na ihu e. Na ịhụnẹnya,
English Translation: For he chose us in him before the creation of the world to be holy and blameless in his sight. In love

Transcript: Chineke kwadeberi ayị na ayị je-abụ ụmụ ọ garị nwa a Jisọs Karaịs mụbata, na nke ọ tọrụ a ụtọ, bụkọrụ ọchụchọ obu e.
English Translation: He predestined us for adoption to sonship through Jesus Christ, in accordance with his pleasure and will—

Transcript: Na o weteri e otuto maka ẹwụọma a dị ebube, bụ nke ọ garị ẹka Onyem ọ hụrụ na ẹnya bụ Ọkpara a me ya o ru ayị ẹka na amaka.
English Translation: to the praise of his glorious grace, which he has freely given us in the One he loves.

Transcript: Ayị nwoteri mgbafụta na ime Karaịs hite na mee ye, a gbaharị ayị ihe ọjọọ aayị,na usoro nke oke ẹwụọma Chineke,
English Translation: In him we have redemption through his blood, the forgiveness of sins, in accordance with the riches of God’s grace

Transcript: ọ gbaarị ayị na ibe o hiri ne ọkam na amamihie yaa ngọta.
English Translation: that he lavished on us. With all wisdom and understanding,

Transcript: Chineke jiri amamihie yaa ngọta a kpuheeri ayị ihe omimi nke ụzọ a, bụ nke tọrụ a ụtọ na omume, nke o hiworuri kwadebe imezu hite na ẹka Karaịs.
English Translation: he made known to us the mystery of his will according to his good pleasure, which he purposed in Christ,

Transcript: Nke o je-otiye na ọrụ na mgbe ogie ruru, iwete ihe ọọbụla na ohu nke dị na elugwe maa na elụwa, na okpuru onye isi aanị, bụkwanụ Karaịs.
English Translation: to be put into effect when the times reach their fulfillment—to bring unity to all things in heaven and on earth under Christ.

Transcript: Chineke họtarị ayị na ime Karaịs dịka nke o hiworuri tụa na ọ je-ọdị, dịka nke ọ dị na atụmatụ yaoni bụ Chineke onye na-arụ ihe ọọbụla na ohu na nke evum na obu e yaa ọchụchọ a dị.
English Translation: In him we were also chosen, having been predestined according to the plan of him who works out everything in conformity with the purpose of his will,

Transcript: Ma a ga ya ẹɦụm na ayịa ndie buru ụzọ nwoe olile-ẹnya na Karaịs bụrụ nde je-eweteri Chineke otuto na ime ịdị ebubie.
English Translation: in order that we, who were the first to put our hope in Christ, might be for the praise of his glory.

Transcript: Unu bụkọ nde e tiyekoworu na ndeke Chineke ẹka unu nụrụ ya eziokwu nke oziọmam, bụ ihe e jiri zọfụta unu. Unu kweye na ya, nwoe ntụkwasịobu na ibe Karaịs nọ, Chineke weri Maa Nsọ a o kweri na nkwa kachie unu akara,
English Translation: And you also were included in Christ when you heard the message of truth, the gospel of your salvation. When you believed, you were marked in him with a seal, the promised Holy Spirit,

Transcript: bụkwanụ yaa Maa Nsọm bụ onye mkpalẹka igusi na nkwa Chineke kweri ndekie je-eru ayị ẹka, na mgbafụta ndeke Chineke je-ezu oke, na e toe Chineke Onye dị ebube.
English Translation: who is a deposit guaranteeing our inheritance until the redemption of those who are God’s possession—to the praise of his glory.

Transcript: Ọ bụ a meri, ẹka m nụrụ bayeri otue okwukwe unu nwo na ibe Onyenwoayị Jisọs nọ, yeri otue ịhụnẹnya unu nwo na ibe ụmụ Chineke nọ,
English Translation: For this reason, ever since I heard about your faith in the Lord Jesus and your love for all God’s people,

Transcript: aka m nọm na-ekele Chineke maka unu, na-arịta unu na ekpere.
English Translation: I have not stopped giving thanks for you, remembering you in my prayers.

Transcript: Ihe m na-arịa mgbe ọọbụla bụ na Chineke nke Onyenwoayị Jisọs Karaịs, Nna dị ebube, weri Maa nke amamihe yaa mkpuhe nịa unu na unu machaarị onye Chineke bụ.
English Translation: I keep asking that the God of our Lord Jesus Christ, the glorious Father, may give you the Spirit[f] of wisdom and revelation, so that you may know him better.

Transcript: Ekpere m bụkọ na ime obu uunu mehee ma unu marị ihe bụ olile-ẹnya ihe Chineke kwobe ku unu, ihe bụ ya ihe omimim dị ebube o debeeri ndekie, wo je-eri na ekpe,
English Translation: I pray that the eyes of your heart may be enlightened in order that you may know the hope to which he has called you, the riches of his glorious inheritance in his holy people,

Transcript: na unu matakọ ya ikikem nke Chineke aadịgị ihe e ji na-atụyekoru e na ibe ayịande tụkwasịrị a obu nọ. Ya ikikem Chineke ji na-arụ ọrụ bụ ihe na-arụ ọrụ na ime ayị,
English Translation: and his incomparably great power for us who believe. That power is the same as the mighty strength

Transcript: bụ ikike Chineke jiri me Karaịs ya o hi na ọnwụ pavuru, je-anọdụa ọdụ na ẹka ikenge yaoni bụ Chineke na ime elugwe.
English Translation: he exerted when he raised Christ from the dead and seated him at his right hand in the heavenly realms,

Transcript: Karaịs nọ na ibe dị na elu karịa ọchịchị isi ọọbụla, karịa ikike yaa mkpalẹka ọọbụla, karịa ihe ọọbụla a na-echi echi; ọ bụgụnwa na ọnwa mbụ ụwa, kama maa na ọmụ mbụ ụwa ka je-abịanị.
English Translation: far above all rule and authority, power and dominion, and every name that is invoked, not only in the present age but also in the one to come.

Transcript: Chineke weri ihe ọọbụla na ohu debie na okpuru ọkpa, me ya ọ bụrụ a bụ isi ihe ọọbụla na ohu na chọchị,
English Translation: And God placed all things under his feet and appointed him to be head over everything for the church,

Transcript: bụ ụhụ a, ezumokie bụ onye na-emejufute ihe ọọbụla na ohu na ụzọ ọọbụla.
English Translation: which is his body, the fullness of him who fills everything in every way.

Transcript: Na mgbe garị aga, unu bụrụ nde nwụhụrụ anwụhụ na ime ndụ ọjọọ uunu yaa enufuru Chineke isi,
English Translation: As for you, you were dead in your transgressions and sins,

Transcript: bụ otue ndụ unu nọrụ na-ebu maka na unu nọrụ na-eso ụzọ nke ụwa, nọdụa na okpuru onye ọchịchị nke eluwaa bụ Ekwensu, bụ maa nọ na ọrụ na ime ndem na ohu eeru beerigi Chineke isi.
English Translation: in which you used to live when you followed the ways of this world and of the ruler of the kingdom of the air, the spirit who is now at work in those who are disobedient.

Transcript: Ayị buwokoru ya otue ndụm na etiti wo na mgbe garị aga, na-egbo ẹgụ ihe ọjọọ na ohu gụrụ anụhụ aayị, hite na ime ihe ọọbụla gbabatarị ayị na obu. Dịka nde ọzọzọm, ayị bụrụ nde ikpe maworu nọrụ na-eche mgbe iwe-ọkụ Chineke je-adakwasị ayị.
English Translation: All of us also lived among them at one time, gratifying the cravings of our flesh and following its desires and thoughts. Like the rest, we were by nature deserving of wrath.

Transcript: Ọbụ, maka oke ịhụnẹnya Chineke na ibe ayị nọ, onye na-ahụŋarị onyimee,
English Translation: But because of his great love for us, God, who is rich in mercy,

Transcript: ya o me ayị dị ndụ ayịa Karaịs bụwakwanụarị nde nwụhụrụ anwụhụ na ime ihe ọjọọ aayị. Ọ bụ ẹwụọma Chineke meri a zọfụta unu.
English Translation: made us alive with Christ even when we were dead in transgressions—it is by grace you have been saved.

Transcript: Chineke kuvutekote ayịa Karaịs na ọnwụ, me ayị nọdụkọta ayịa Karaịs Jisọs na elugwe.
English Translation: And God raised us up with Christ and seated us with him in the heavenly realms in Christ Jesus,

Transcript: Chineke meri e ya ẹɦụa ma o jiri e gusi ụmụ madụ na ụwa ka abịataje abịa ohihine ẹwụọma a hiri, nke o gusiri na obuọma o mesoru ayị na ọnwụ Karaịs Jisọs nwụhụụrụ ayị.
English Translation: in order that in the coming ages he might show the incomparable riches of his grace, expressed in his kindness to us in Christ Jesus.

Transcript: Maka na ọ bụ ẹwụọma Chineke meri a zọfụta ayị hite na ntụkwasịobu na ibe Karaịs nọ. O hidigi unu na ẹka mbụ nzọfụta uunu, ọ bụ ihe Chineke yaẹkaa nịrị na amaka.
English Translation: For it is by grace you have been saved, through faith—and this is not from yourselves, it is the gift of God—

Transcript: Ọ bụdịgị ihe e meri na nke madụ garị rụkebe ọrụ ike, na ọ dịkwa onye je-eji e baa mba.
English Translation: not by works, so that no one can boast.

Transcript: Maka na ayị bụ ọrụ ẹka Chineke, nde e kegeriworu na ime Karaịs Jisọs ịrụ ọrụ ọma bụ nke Chineke hiworuri kie ye na ọ dị.
English Translation: For we are God’s handiwork, created in Christ Jesus to do good works, which God prepared in advance for us to do.

Transcript: Unu rịta na mgbe garị aga na unuande bụ nde aabụgụ nde Juu bụ nde a nọrụ na-ekuu “Nde eesegi ọnụ-utu,” mbụ ndem na-eku onwowo, “Nde e seri ọnụ-utu,” bụkwanụ ihe e meri na anụhụ.
English Translation: Therefore, remember that formerly you who are Gentiles by birth and called “uncircumcised” by those who call themselves “the circumcision” (which is done in the body by human hands)—

Transcript: Unu rịta na ya mgbem na unu bụrụ nde nọrụ na-ebu ndụ wo na amagị Karaịs, nde a kpafụrụ na ọbụbụ nde alị Izirẹlụ, bụrụ nde mba ọzọ eenwogu oke ọọbụla na nkwam nke ọgbụgbandụ Chineke kweri wo, bụrụ nde eenwogu olile-ẹnya ọọbụla na ụwa, nwokogu Chineke.
English Translation: remember that at that time you were separate from Christ, excluded from citizenship in Israel and foreigners to the covenants of the promise, without hope and without God in the world.

Transcript: Ọbụ ẹɦụọdị unu nọzu na ime Karaịs Jisọs, unuande bụwaarị nde nọwaarịrị na ibe otele, abụworu nde e wenyebeworu hite na mee Karaịs.
English Translation: But now in Christ Jesus you who once were far away have been brought near by the blood of Christ.

Transcript: Na mbụ ya Okwum dịrị, ya Okwum yaa Chineke nọrụ, ya Okwum bụrụ Chineke.
English Translation: In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God.

Transcript: Ya Okwum yaa Chineke nọwozururi na isi mbụ mbụ.
English Translation: He was with God in the beginning.

Transcript: Ọ bụ ya Okwum bụ onye Chineke jiri kie ihe oohu o keri eke, ọ dịgị ma ọ bụgụ ihe aanị Chineke keri eke oojidigi ya Okwum kie.
English Translation: Through him all things were made; without him nothing was made that has been made.

Transcript: Ọ bụ na ya Okwum bụ ibe ndụ hi, ọ bụkwanụ ya ndụm bụ ihe chawaarị ụmụ madụ oohu.
English Translation: In him was life, and that life was the light of all mankind.

Transcript: Ya ihem na-acham ẹkamgbe na ime ẹtụlị, ọbụ na ọ dịgị mgbe ẹtụlị menyuru e.
English Translation: The light shines in the darkness, and the darkness has not overcome it.

Transcript: Chineke ziteri nwoke aanị a na-eku Jọn.
English Translation: There was a man sent from God whose name was John.

Transcript: Ọ bịarị ịgba ama bayeri ya ihem chawaarị ụmụ madụ, ma onye ọọbụla nụrụ ozi e nwo ike kwete.
English Translation: He came as a witness to testify concerning that light, so that through him all might believe.

Transcript: Jọn yaẹkaa abụgụ ya ihem, kama ọ bịarịnwa ịgba ama bayeri ya ihem.
English Translation: He himself was not the light; he came only as a witness to the light.

Transcript: Ya ezibe ihem na-acharị madụ oohu gabatarị na ụwa.
English Translation: The true light that gives light to everyone was coming into the world. \

Transcript: Ya Okwum nọrụ na ụwa, na-agbayekokwegiri na Chineke jiri e kie ihe ọọbụla na ụwa, ka nde nọ na ụwa aamatadị onye ọ bụ.
English Translation: He was in the world, and though the world was made through him, the world did not recognize him.

Transcript: Ọ bịarị na ibe nkie, ka ndekie aanabata a.
English Translation: He came to that which was his own, but his own did not receive him.

Transcript: Ọbụ na nke woha bụ ndem nabatarị anị, ndem kweteri na ẹha a, bụ nde ọ nịrị ikike je-eme na wo abụrụ ụmụ Chineke.
English Translation: Yet to all who did receive him, to those who believed in his name, he gave the right to become children of God—

Transcript: Wo abụgụnwa nde a mụrụ na eriri madụ amaka, a mụrụ na mkpebu madụ ka ẹɦụm madụ na-aga mụa nwa, kama wo bụ nde Chineke meri wo bụrụ ụmụ a.
English Translation: children born not of natural descent, nor of human decision or a husband’s will, but born of God.

Transcript: Ya Okwum medueri bụrụ madụ, nworu anụhụ buru na etiti aayị. Ayị ahụwo ebubie, ebube Nna nịrị a bụ Ọkpara aanị O nwo. Ndụ a jufuteri na ẹwụọma yaa eziokwu.
English Translation: The Word became flesh and made his dwelling among us. We have seen his glory, the glory of the one and only Son, who came from the Father, full of grace and truth.

Transcript: Jọn gbarị ama bayeri e, sị, “Onyie bụ onyem m kwuru okwu e sị, ‘O nworu onye je-emedue bịa, ọ bụ na ọ kaŋaarị m ọkam, maka na o hiworuri nọdụa ta a na-amụ m.’ ”
English Translation: (John testified concerning him. He cried out, saying, “This is the one I spoke about when I said, ‘He who comes after me has surpassed me because he was before me.’”)

Transcript: Jisọs zuru oke maa ụma na ẹwụọma. Hite na ẹwụọma a, ayị natarị ngọzi na elu ngọzi.
English Translation: Out of his fullness we have all received grace in place of grace already given.

Transcript: Chineke garị ẹka Mosisi nị ụmụ madụ iwu e, ọbụ na ẹwụọma yaa eziokwu oohu garị ẹka Jisọs Karaịs bịa.
English Translation: For the law was given through Moses; grace and truth came through Jesus Christ.

Transcript: Ọ ka ọ dịtụgụ onye hụtụworu Chineke ẹnya. Ọ bụ onye yaanịa bụ Ọkpara Chineke, onye yaẹkaa bụkọm Chineke, nọ Nna na ẹkụkụ, ọ bụ a kpuheeri ayị onye Chineke bụ.
English Translation: No one has ever seen God, but the one and only Son, who is himself God and is in closest relationship with the Father, has made him known.

Transcript: Jọn ome baụtizim gbaa ama mgbe nde ọchịchị nde Juu na Jerusalẹm dufuru nde ọchụẹja maa nde hi na eriri Livaị wo jekwu e je-ajụ a, “Ọ bụ gụ bụ onye?”
English Translation: Now this was John’s testimony when the Jewish leaders in Jerusalem sent priests and Levites to ask him who he was.

Transcript: Jọn jaa ọnụ aja sị wo, “Ọ bụgụ m bụ Karaịs.”
English Translation: He did not fail to confess, but confessed freely, “I am not the Messiah.”

Transcript: Wo jụ a, “Ọ bụkwanụ gụ bụ onye? Ị bụ onye amụma Ịlaịja?” Ya ọ sị wo, “Waa! Abụgụ m.” Wo jụkwakwa a, “Ọ bụ gụ bụ ya onye amụmam?” Jọn sịkwa wori, “Waa!”
English Translation: They asked him, “Then who are you? Are you Elijah?” He said, “I am not.” “Are you the Prophet?” He answered, “No.”

Transcript: Wo sịzu e, “Ọ bụkwanụ gụ bụ onye? Karị ayị ihe ayị je-asị nde duyeri ayị ozi. Ị sị gịnị bayeri onwogu?”
English Translation: Finally they said, “Who are you? Give us an answer to take back to those who sent us. What do you say about yourself?”

Transcript: Jọn weri ihe onye amụma Ayịzaya kwuru saa wo e sị, “Ọ bụ m bụ ya olu onye aanịm na-adaa na ọzara, ‘Mechee okporo ụzọ Onyenwoayị na o guzo kpororo.’ ”
English Translation: John replied in the words of Isaiah the prophet, “I am the voice of one calling in the wilderness, ‘Make straight the way for the Lord.’”[d]

Transcript: Ndem e duyeri ozi bụrụ nde Farisii,
English Translation: Now the Pharisees who had been sent

Transcript: jụkwakwazu Jọn, “Ọ bụkwanụ gịnị meri i na-ime nde madụ baụtizim ma gị abụgụ Karaịs, bụgụ Ịlaịja, bụkọkwanụgụ ya onye amụmam?”
English Translation: questioned him, “Why then do you baptize if you are not the Messiah, nor Elijah, nor the Prophet?”

Transcript: Jọn sị wo, “Eji m mini na-eme baụtizim, ọ bụ na o nworu onye guzo na etiti uunu unu aamagị onye ọ bụ.
English Translation: “I baptize with[e] water,” John replied, “but among you stands one you do not know.

Transcript: Ọ bụ a bụ ya onyem je-esochi m azụ bịa, aka m eruko[1]heegi ịtọsị eriri akpụkpọkpa a.”
English Translation: He is the one who comes after me, the straps of whose sandals I am not worthy to untie.”

Transcript: Ihie na ohu gbarị na Betani dịnyabarị ẹnyụm Jọdan ibe Jọn nọrụ na-eme nde madụ baụtizim.
English Translation: This all happened at Bethany on the other side of the Jordan, where John was baptizing.

Transcript: Ya o rue ụbọɦụụya, Jọn ome baụtizim hụ Jisọs ibe o hiri bịataje na ibe ọ nọrụ, ya ọ sị, “Ị hụ nwa atụrụ Chineke, na-ewelehi mmehie ụmụ ụwa!
English Translation: The next day John saw Jesus coming toward him and said, “Look, the Lamb of God, who takes away the sin of the world!

Transcript: Ọ bụ a bụ onyem m sịrị unu, ‘O nworu onye je-esochi m azụ bịa karịrị mnị, maka na o hiworuri nọdụa ta a mụa m.’
English Translation: This is the one I meant when I said, ‘A man who comes after me has surpassed me because he was before me.’

Transcript: Mụẹkam amadịgị onye ọ bụ, ọbụ na-abịarị m bịa-ejiri mini na-eme baụtizim, ma e kpuheeri Izirẹlụ onye ọ bụ.”
English Translation: I myself did not know him, but the reason I came baptizing with water was that he might be revealed to Israel.”

Transcript: Jọn gbakọa ama sị, “Ahụrụ m Maa Nsọ hi na elugwe kpọride ka nnụnụ ẹkpala bịa-eberi e na ụhụ.
English Translation: Then John gave this testimony: “I saw the Spirit come down from heaven as a dove and remain on him.

Transcript: Amagị m amatawaarịrị onye ọ bụ ma ya ọ bụgụ na onyem duyeri m bịa-eweri mini meje baụtizim sịrị m, ‘Onyem ị je-ịhụ Maa Nsọ je-ebekwesi na ụhụ bụ a bụ ya onyem je-eji Maa Nsọ mie nkie mbụ baụtizim.’
English Translation: And I myself did not know him, but the one who sent me to baptize with water told me, ‘The man on whom you see the Spirit come down and remain is the one who will baptize with the Holy Spirit.’

Transcript: Ahụwo mu e, na-agba ama na ọ bụ a bụ Ọkpara Chineke.”
English Translation: I have seen and I testify that this is God’s Chosen One.”

Transcript: Ya o rue na ụbọɦụụya, Jọn guzoru yaa nde na-eso ụzọ a madụ ẹbọọ.
English Translation: The next day John was there again with two of his disciples.

Transcript: Wo hụ Jisọs ibe ọ gabugeje, Jọn sị, “Unu ahụ nwa atụrụ Chineke!”
English Translation: When he saw Jesus passing by, he said, “Look, the Lamb of God!”

Transcript: Mgbe nde na-eso ụzọ Jọn woa madụ ẹbọọ nụrụ ihe Jọn kwuru, wo pavuru sojeje Jisọs azụ azụ.
English Translation: When the two disciples heard him say this, they followed Jesus.

Transcript: Jisọs tụgarịa, sị wo, “Unu na-achọ gịnị?” Wo sị a, “Rabaị, ndaa ibe i bu?” Ya okwum fụtarị “Onye ozizi.”
English Translation: Turning around, Jesus saw them following and asked, “What do you want?” They said, “Rabbi” (which means “Teacher”), “where are you staying?”

Transcript: Jisọs sị wo, “Unu bịa-elegi ibe ọ bụ.” Wo so e na-eje, je-ahụ ibe ọ bụ, nọdụzue woa ya ya izukum gabu-gefuu. Ọ bụrụ atam ẹnọ na ehihe nọrụ na-akụ mgbe woa Jisọs yịrị jege na ibe ọ nọ.
English Translation: “Come,” he replied, “and you will see.” So they went and saw where he was staying, and they spent that day with him. It was about four in the afternoon.

Transcript: Anduru bụrụ nwane nwoke Saịmọn Pita sokoru na ya madụm ẹbọọ nụrụ ihe Jọn kwuru, soru Jisọs je-amata ibe ọ nọ.
English Translation: Andrew, Simon Peter’s brother, was one of the two who heard what John had said and who had followed Jesus.

Transcript: Ya o me Anduru zavuru je-achọa nwanie nwoke Saịmọn, sị a, “Ayị ahụwo Mezaya” (fụtarị Karaịs).
English Translation: The first thing Andrew did was to find his brother Simon and tell him, “We have found the Messiah” (that is, the Christ).

Transcript: Anduru duru Saịmọn nwanie na-ejekwu Jisọs. Mgbe wo jekwuteri e, Jisọs le Saịmọn ẹnya sị a, “Ọ bụ gụ bụ Saịmọn nwa Jọn, hite ẹɦụọdị e je na-eku gu Kefas.” Ọ bụ a bụ Pita fụtarị “mkpume”.
English Translation: And he brought him to Jesus. Jesus looked at him and said, “You are Simon son of John. You will be called Cephas” (which, when translated, is Peter).

Transcript: Ya o rue na ụbọɦụụya, Jisọs pavuru hi na Galili na-asọhụ. Ya ọ hụ Filipu sị a, “So m!”
English Translation: The next day Jesus decided to leave for Galilee. Finding Philip, he said to him, “Follow me.”

Transcript: Filipu bụkọrụ onye Bẹtịsaịda bụ ibe nke Anduru yaa Pita nwanie.
English Translation: Philip, like Andrew and Peter, was from the town of Bethsaida.

Transcript: Filipu je-achọvụta Natanịẹl sị a, “Ayị ahụwo onyem Mosisi deri bayeri na ẹkwụkwọ Iwu, nde amụma dekoe ihe bayeri e. Ọ bụ a bụ Jisọs nwa Josẹf, onye Nazarẹtị.”
English Translation: Philip found Nathanael and told him, “We have found the one Moses wrote about in the Law, and about whom the prophets also wrote—Jesus of Nazareth, the son of Joseph.”

Transcript: Natanịẹl sị a, “Nazarẹtị! Ihe dị ma o nworu ike ihi na Nazarẹtị fụta?” Filipu sị a, “Bịa-eweri ẹnya gị hụkọzu em.”
English Translation: “Nazareth! Can anything good come from there?” Nathanael asked. “Come and see,” said Philip.

Transcript: Mgbe Jisọs hụrụ Natanịẹl yaa Filipu ibe wo yị bịataje, Jisọs kwue bayeri Natanịẹl sị, “Unu ahụ ezibe nwa Izirẹlụ, onye aadịgị ụgọrọ dị a na ime.”
English Translation: When Jesus saw Nathanael approaching, he said of him, “Here truly is an Israelite in whom there is no deceit.”  “How do you know me?”

Transcript: Natanịẹl sị a, “Ị garị ẹgaa marị ihe bayeri m?” Jisọs sị a, “Ahụrụ m gụ na mgbem i guzoru na ukwu osisi Figi, ta Filipu bịataje gi okuku.”
English Translation: Nathanael asked. Jesus answered, “I saw you while you were still under the fig tree before Philip called you.”

Transcript: Natanịẹl sị a, “Rabaị, ọ bụ gụ bụ Ọkpara Chineke, bụkwanụ Eze ụmụ Izirẹlụ!”
English Translation: Then Nathanael declared, “Rabbi, you are the Son of God; you are the king of Israel.”

Transcript: Jisọs sị a, “I kwetezuru na-abụ m onye dị ya ẹɦụm, maka na-asị m gị na-ahụrụ m gụ mgbe i guzo na ukwu osisi figi? I ka eje-ahụ ihe dịga izize karịa ya ọnwa.”
English Translation: Jesus said, “You believe because I told you I saw you under the fig tree. You will see greater things than that.”

Transcript: Jisọs sị wo, “Na eziokwu na eziokwu asị m unu, unu je-ahụ mgbe elugwe je-ekpuhe, maa nke nde maaozi Chineke je na-enyikoru na-akpọride na elu Nwa Nke Madụ.”
English Translation: He then added, “Very truly I tell you, you will see ‘heaven open, and the angels of God ascending and descending on’ the Son of Man.”

Transcript: O Tiofilọs, na ẹkwụ kwọ mbụ m, e deri m bayeri ihe Jisọs maliteri na-eme, na-eziko
English Translation: In my former book, Theophilus, I wrote about all that Jesus began to do and to teach

Transcript: tututu rue izuku e kukooru e na elugwe. Ta e kukoru e, o jiri ikike Maa Nsọ ziduhee ndeozi e, ndem ọ họtarị ihe wo je-eme.
English Translation: until the day he was taken up to heaven, after giving instructions through the Holy Spirit to the apostles he had chosen.

Transcript: Na mgbe ọ tadụworu ahụhụ nwụhụ, ta hi na ọnwụ pavuru, o gusiri wo onwoe, weri ntụtụ ihe aamagị agbaga agbaga gusi wo na ọ dị ndụ. O gusiri wo onwoe ihe ruru ihu abalị ẹbọọ, na-ekwuru wo ihe bayeri Alịeze Chineke.
English Translation: After his suffering, he presented himself to them and gave many convincing proofs that he was alive. He appeared to them over a period of forty days and spoke about the kingdom of God.

Transcript: Na mgbe aanị yaa wo ka anọrụ, ya ọ sị wo, “Unu ehikwe na Jerusalẹm sọhụ, kama unu cheri ya ihom Nna m kweri unu na nkwa na o je-anị unu, dịka nke unu nụworu e na ọnụ m.
English Translation: On one occasion, while he was eating with them, he gave them this command: “Do not leave Jerusalem, but wait for the gift my Father promised, which you have heard me speak about.

Transcript: Maka na Jọn jiri mini amaka na-eme baụtizim, na abalịa olenwe bịanị, a je-eji Maa Nsọ mie unu baụtizim.”
English Translation: For John baptized with water, but in a few days you will be baptized with the Holy Spirit.”

Transcript: Na mgbe wo nọkọtarị, ndeozi e jụ a, “Onyenwoayị, ọ bụ ẹɦụọdị bụ mgbe i ji je-ewehechi ọchịchị na ẹka nde Izirẹlụ?”
English Translation: Then they gathered around him and asked him, “Lord, are you at this time going to restore the kingdom to Israel?”

Transcript: Jisọs sị wo, “Ọ dịịrịgị unu ịmata ya izukum, ma ọ bụgụ ya mgbem ọ je-ọbụ, maka na ọ bụ Nna yaanịa bụ onye ya ọmụ dị na ẹka.
English Translation: He said to them: “It is not for you to know the times or dates the Father has set by his own authority.

Transcript: Ọbụ na unu je-anata ikike na mgbe Maa Nsọ je-abịa kwasị unu; na unu abụrụ nde ama m na Jerusalẹm, maa na Judia yaa Sameria tututu gazue elụwa na ohu rue na ibe ọ sọtụrụ.”
English Translation: But you will receive power when the Holy Spirit comes on you; and you will be my witnesses in Jerusalem, and in all Judea and Samaria, and to the ends of the earth.”

Transcript: Na mgbe Jisọs kwuduuru wo ya ẹɦụm, wo na elie ẹnya, e kuhee ye nyikoru elugwe, ka wo aahụsị a, ẹnwụrọkụ elugwe kpuchie ye.
English Translation: After he said this, he was taken up before their very eyes, and a cloud hid him from their sight.

Transcript: Na ya mgbem Jisọs nyikojeri na elugwe, ndeozi e na ohu chịrị ẹnya wụtọba a ẹɦụm o nyikojeri. Ndikom ẹbọọ yege uwe ọcha kwe gọdịm bịa eguzonyebe wo.
English Translation: They were looking intently up into the sky as he was going, when suddenly two men dressed in white stood beside them.

Transcript: Ya ndem bịarị bịa-eguzonyebe wo sị wo, “Ndikom nde Galili, ọ bụ gịnị meri unu guzo na ibie na ele ẹnya na elugwe? Ya Jisọsụa unu hụrụ e kuneheri unu kukoru elugwe ka je-ehikweri na elugwe kpọride ẹɦụa unu hụrụ a ọ garị nyikoru.”
English Translation: “Men of Galilee,” they said, “why do you stand here looking into the sky? This same Jesus, who has been taken from you into heaven, will come back in the same way you have seen him go into heaven.”

Transcript: Ndeozi Jisọs hi na ugwu Olivu garị na-alahachi Jerusalẹm. Hite na ya ibom dịrị ihe dịka mkpiri maịnị na e rute Jerusalẹm.
English Translation: Then the apostles returned to Jerusalem from the hill called the Mount of Olives, a Sabbath day’s walk from the city.

Transcript: Na mgbe wo waruteri, wo garị je-enyikoru na elu uloelu aanị je-anọdụkọta. Nde nọrụ na ya ibom bụrụ, Pita, Jọn, Jems yaa Anduru, Filipu yaa Tọmọs, Batịlomi yaa Matiu, Jems nwa Alịfịọs, yeri Saịmọn bụrụonye otu ndem na-alụchiteri nde ọzọ aga, yekozuru Judas nwa Jems.
English Translation: When they arrived, they went upstairs to the room where they were staying. Those present were Peter, John, James and Andrew; Philip and Thomas, Bartholomew and Matthew; James son of Alphaeus and Simon the Zealot, and Judas son of James.

Transcript: Wo oohu nọkọtarị na ya ibom, na-ekpe ekpere mgbe ọọbụla, woa nde nwanyị; maa Meri ne Jisọs yaa ụmụne Jisọs nde nwoke.
English Translation: They all joined together constantly in prayer, along with the women and Mary the mother of Jesus, and with his brothers.

Transcript: Ya o rue na izuku aanị, Pita pavuru guzo na etiti ya ndem na-eso ụzọ Jisọs nọkọtarị na ya ibom, wo dịrị ihe dịka ihu madụ isii.
English Translation: In those days Peter stood up among the believers (a group numbering about a hundred and twenty)

Transcript: Pita sị, “Ụmụnna, ihe e deri na Ẹkwụkwọ Nsọ je-emezuriri ẹɦụm Maa Nsọ kwuru e ẹkamgbe na ọnụ Devidi bayeri Judas, onye duru ndem jeri je-egide Jisọs.
English Translation: and said, “Brothers and sisters, the Scripture had to be fulfilled in which the Holy Spirit spoke long ago through David concerning Judas, who served as guide for those who arrested Jesus.

Transcript: O sokorunwe ayị, sokoru jie ozie nke Onyenwoayị.”
English Translation: He was one of our number and shared in our ministry.”

Transcript: Judas weeri ya okpogo arụrụ alịm ọ natarị wo je-azụta alị, bụ ibe ọ darị tọgbọrụ, ẹhọ gbafuruhu e, akịrẹhọ a nunufute.
English Translation: (With the payment he received for his wickedness, Judas bought a field; there he fell headlong, his body burst open and all his intestines spilled out.

Transcript: Madụ oohu nọ na Jerusalẹm nụrụ bayeri e, wo gụba ya alịm Judas zụrụ Akẹlụdema na okwu wo, nke fụtarị “Alị mee”.
English Translation: Everyone in Jerusalem heard about this, so they called that field in their language Akeldama, that is, Field of Blood.)

Transcript: Pita sị, “E deri e na ẹkwụkwọ ẹbụọma na Ẹkwụkwọ Nsọ sị, “ ‘Na ulo e tọgbọrụ kpokorojam; gbaa ọtụrụ, na madụ ebukwe na ya.’ “Na ibe ọzọkwakwa, e die, “ ‘Na onye ọzọ nọchie ye na ozie.’
English Translation: “For,” said Peter, “it is written in the Book of Psalms: “ ‘May his place be deserted; let there be no one to dwell in it,’and, “ ‘May another take his place of leadership.’

Transcript: “Ọ bụ a meri ayị je-ahọta onye aanị na nde nwokie so ayị ẹkamgbie ayịa Onyenwoayị Jisọs yị na-agagarị.
English Translation: Therefore it is necessary to choose one of the men who have been with us the whole time the Lord Jesus was living among us,

Transcript: Hiteri na mgbem Jọn maliteri ejem-ozi nke baụtizim tututu rue mgbem e kukooru Jisọs na elugwe. Maka na onye aanị na ime wo je-esokoriri ayị bụrụ onye je-agba ama bayeri apavuru na ọnwụ Jisọs.”
English Translation: beginning from John’s baptism to the time when Jesus was taken up from us. For one of these must become a witness with us of his resurrection.”

Transcript: Ya ome, wo wefute nde nwoke ẹbọọ bụ Josẹf a na-eku Basabas ma ọ bụgụ Jọstus yaa Matịas.
English Translation: So they nominated two men: Joseph called Barsabbas (also known as Justus) and Matthias.

Transcript: Wo kpie ekpere sị, “Onyenwoayị, ọ dịgị onye ịịmagị obu e. Gusi ayị na ime madụa ẹbọọ, onye ị họtarị,
English Translation: Then they prayed, “Lord, you know everyone’s heart. Show us which of these two you have chosen

Transcript: je-anọchi ọnọdụ dịka onyeozi nke Onyenwoayị, Judas gbaŋakọrụ garị jege ibom bụ ibe o so.”
English Translation: to take over this apostolic ministry, which Judas left to go where he belongs.”

Transcript: Wo tụa okwe, ya ọ dayeri Matịas; ya o sokozuru madụm irile nnanị fọrụ afọ bụkọzuru onyeozi nke Onyenwoayị
English Translation: Then they cast lots, and the lot fell to Matthias; so he was added to the eleven apostles

Transcript: Na mgbe o ruru na izuku mmemme a na-eku Pentikọsụtụ, ndem na ohu bụ nde na-eso ụzọ Onyenwoayị nọkọtarị na ibe aanị.
English Translation: When the day of Pentecost came, they were all together in one place.

Transcript: Na mberede, ụda dịka oke ihuhe hi na elugwe malite na-adasi ike, bịa-eju ya ime ulom wo nọrụ ọdụ.
English Translation: Suddenly a sound like the blowing of a violent wind came from heaven and filled the whole house where they were sitting.

Transcript: Wo hụ ihe dịrị ka ire ọkụ bịarị bịa ekewesidue bịa-ebiekwesidue onyeaha na isi nnanị nnanị.
English Translation: They saw what seemed to be tongues of fire that separated and came to rest on each of them.

Transcript: A gbajue nke woha na Maa Nsọ, wo malite na-asụgazu okwu mba dịga iche iche, dịka nke Maa Nsọ nịrị wo ikike.
English Translation: All of them were filled with the Holy Spirit and began to speak in other tongues as the Spirit enabled them.

Transcript: Na ya mgbem, o nworu ntụtụ nde Juu, nde na-ekperi Chineke, higeri na mba oohu dịga iche iche na elụwa bịa-eburu na Jerusalẹm.
English Translation: Now there were staying in Jerusalem God-fearing Jews from every nation under heaven.

Transcript: Mgbe wo nụrụ ụzụ ihom nde na-eso ụzọ Jisọs nọrụ na-ekwu, wo nukporu na-eje elete ihe na-agbanị. Ya ọ gbagwojukote wo ẹnya maka na wo nọrụ na-anụ ibe wo nọrụ na-asụ okwu nde alịm wo higeri bịa na Jerusalẹm.
English Translation: When they heard this sound, a crowd came together in bewilderment, because each one heard their own language being spoken.

Transcript: Ya o jukote wo ẹnya ọkam, wo na-ajụ: “Ndie na ohu na-asụ ihie abụgagị nde Galili?
English Translation: Utterly amazed, they asked: “Aren’t all these who are speaking Galileans?

Transcript: Ndakwanụa nke wo garị na-asụgazu okwu alị aayịga ayị na[1]anụ?
English Translation: Then how is it that each of us hears them in our native language?

Transcript: Maa nde hi na Patịa, maa nde Mẹdẹ, maa nde Ẹlam, maa nde Mesopotomia, maa nde Judia, maa nde Kapadoshia, maa nde Pọntus, maa nde Eshia,
English Translation: Parthians, Medes and Elamites; residents of Mesopotamia, Judea and Cappadocia, Pontus and Asia,

Transcript: maa nde Firigia, maa nde Pamufilia, maa nde Ijiputu, maa nde hige na ndaga Libia dịnyabarị Sayịrin, maa nde ẹbịa higeri Rom,
English Translation: Phrygia and Pamphylia, Egypt and the parts of Libya near Cyrene; visitors from Rome

Transcript: maa nde Juu woa nde mba ọzọ sokozuru na okpukpe nde Juu, maa nde Kiriti, maa nde Arabụ; ayị na-anụtum ibe wo na-ekwufute oke ihe Chineke na-arụga na okwu aayị!”
English Translation: (both Jews and converts to Judaism); Cretans and Arabs—we hear them declaring the wonders of God in our own tongues!”

Transcript: Ya ọ ju wo ẹnya ọkam, wo na-ajụtarị onwowo, “Ọ bụ gịnị bụ ihe ihie fụtarị?”
English Translation: Amazed and perplexed, they asked one another, “What does this mean?”

Transcript: Ụfọdị weri ya ndem na-eso ụzọ Jisọs na-eme ihe ọchị, na-asịga, “Wo anwụwo mayị nwụkpọsịdụa ẹnya.”
English Translation: Some, however, made fun of them and said, “They have had too much wine.”

Transcript: Ọbụ na Pita pavuuru guzo, yaa ndeozi Jisọs madụ irile nnanịmfụ, jiri oke olu sị ya ndem gbakọtarịnị: “Ndeke ayị nde Juu, maa madụ oohu bu na Jerusalẹm, na mụ akachaarị unu, unu gebe ntị na ihe m je je-ekwu.
English Translation: Then Peter stood up with the Eleven, raised his voice and addressed the crowd: “Fellow Jews and all of you who live in Jerusalem, let me explain this to you; listen carefully to what I say.

Transcript: Ndie unu hụrụ adịgị mayị wo nwụrụ ẹɦụm unu na-arịị. Ọ ka ọ bụnụnwa atam tolu na ụtụtụ.
English Translation: These people are not drunk, as you suppose. It’s only nine in the morning!

Transcript: Kama ihie bụ ihom onye amụma Juwẹlụ kwuru okwu bayeri:
English Translation: No, this is what was spoken by the prophet Joel:

Transcript: “ ‘Chineke sị, ya o rue na mgbe ikpeazụ, Eje m awụkwasị madụ oohu Maa m. Na nde ụmụ uunu, nde nwoke maa nde nwanyị ana-evu amụma, Na nde ụmụokorọbịa uunu ana-ahụ ẹwaga, Na nde ichie uunu ana-arọ nrọ.
English Translation: “ ‘In the last days, God says, I will pour out my Spirit on all people. Your sons and daughters will prophesy, your young men will see visions, your old men will dream dreams.

Transcript: Eje m awụkwasịkọ ndeozi m, maa nde nwoke maa nde nwanyị, Maa Nsọ m, Eje m awụkwasị wo e na ya mgbem, Na wo ana-evu amụma.
English Translation: Even on my servants, both men and women, I will pour out my Spirit in those days, and they will prophesy.

Transcript: Eje m egusi ihe dị izize na elugwe, eje m egusi ihe ahụma na elụwa: mee yaa ọkụ maa oke ẹnwụrọkụ je na-asụụ.
English Translation: I will show wonders in the heavens above and signs on the earth below, blood and fire and billows of smoke.

Transcript: Ẹnyanwụ je-asụ kelikeli, na ọnwa atụgarịa chaa mee mee. Ta na ya oke ụbọchịm dị ebube nke Onyenwoayị erue.
English Translation: The sun will be turned to darkness and the moon to blood before the coming of the great and glorious day of the Lord.

Transcript: A je-azọfụta onye ọọbụla je-akpọku ẹha Onyenwoayị.’
English Translation: And everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved.’

Transcript: “Ndikom Izirẹlụ, unu gebechee ntị: Jisọs onye Nazarẹtị, bụrụ onye Chineke garị ẹka a rụa oke ọrụ ahụma dịga izize gusi na ọ bụ a ziteri e, nke unu makọọrụ unuẹka uunu.
English Translation: “Fellow Israelites, listen to this: Jesus of Nazareth was a man accredited by God to you by miracles, wonders and signs, which God did among you through him, as you yourselves know.

Transcript: A raarị a ye unu na ẹka, dịka Chineke na amamihie hiworuri chobe na ọ bụ nke ọ je-ọdị. Unu garị ẹka nde ụrụalị weri e gbue hite na ikpọgidie na obe.
English Translation: This man was handed over to you by God’s deliberate plan and foreknowledge; and you, with the help of wicked men, put him to death by nailing him to the cross.

Transcript: Ọbụ na Chineke meri e ya o hi na ọnwụ pavuru, hi na ikike ọnwụ fụta, maka na ọ bụ ihe aamagị ekwe omume na ọnwụ je-egidie.
English Translation: But God raised him from the dead, freeing him from the agony of death, because it was impossible for death to keep its hold on him.

Transcript: Devidi kwuru okwu bayeri e sị: “ ‘Ana m ahụ Onyenwoayị na ihu m mgbe ọọbụla. Maka na ọ nọ m na ẹka ikenge, ọ dịgị ihe je-eme m ịsọ ụjọ.
English Translation: David said about him: “ ‘I saw the Lord always before me. Because he is at my right hand, I will not be shaken.

Transcript: Ọ bụ a meri obu dị m ụtọ, okwu m na ohu bụrụ okwu obu-ụtọ; Enworu m olile-ẹnya na ndụ m oohu,
English Translation: Therefore my heart is glad and my tongue rejoices; my body also will rest in hope,

Transcript: maka na ọ dịgị ma ị gbaŋakọ m na alịmaadịgị ma i kwe Onye nsọ gụrehi erehi.
English Translation: because you will not abandon me to the realm of the dead, you will not let your holy one see decay.

Transcript: I mewo m mata ụzọ oohu nke ndụ; i je-ime m na mụ ana-anwụrị ọnwụ na ihu gu.’
English Translation: You have made known to me the paths of life; you will fill me with joy in your presence.’

Transcript: “Ụmụnna, ana m akacharị unu na nnadoche ayị Devidi anwụhụwo, e lie ye, ta ili e ka adịkọnwa na alị aayịa rute taa.
English Translation: “Fellow Israelites, I can tell you confidently that the patriarch David died and was buried, and his tomb is here to this day.

Transcript: Ọbụ na ọ bụrụ onye amụma, marị na Chineke nwụrụ ihe kwie nkwa, na yaoni mbụ Chineke je-eme na onye aanị hi na eriri Devidi abụrụ eze ẹɦụm yaoni bụkọrụ eze.
English Translation: But he was a prophet and knew that God had promised him on oath that he would place one of his descendants on his throne.

Transcript: Ibe ọ bụ na ọ hụworu ihe dị na ihu, ya o kwue bayeri apavuru na ọnwụ Karaịs na mgbem ọ sịrị, na Chineke ahabudigi e na alịmaa, kwegi na ozu e rehi erehi.
English Translation: Seeing what was to come, he spoke of the resurrection of the Messiah, that he was not abandoned to the realm of the dead, nor did his body see decay.

Transcript: Chineke emewo Jisọs ya o hi na ọnwụ pavuru dịkwakwa ndụ, nke ayị oohu bụ nde na-agba ama bayeri e.
English Translation: God has raised this Jesus to life, and we are all witnesses of it.

Transcript: Chineke apakowokoru Jisọs, ya o je je-anọdụa na ẹka ikengie. Ọ natawo ya Maa Nsọm bụ nkwa Nna kweri ịnị ndekie. Ọ bụ a bụ ihe Jisọs wewooru wụsaarị ayị, bụ ihe unu na-ahụ na-anụkọ ẹɦụọdị.
English Translation: Exalted to the right hand of God, he has received from the Father the promised Holy Spirit and has poured out what you now see and hear.

Transcript: Maka na Devidi adịdịgị mgbe o nyikooru na elugwe, ọbụ na ọ sịrị, “ ‘Onyenwoayị sịrị Onyenwo m, Nọdụa ọdụ na ẹka ikenge m
English Translation: For David did not ascend to heaven, and yet he said, “ ‘The Lord said to my Lord: “Sit at my right hand

Transcript: tututu na mụ erehuteri nde-iro gu weri wo meteri gi ibe awụkwasị ọkpa.’ ”
English Translation: until I make your enemies a footstool for your feet.” ’

Transcript: “Ọ bụ a meri na ụmụ Izirẹlụ na ohu matachaanwa, na Chineke emewo Jisọs unu kpọgburu Onyenwoayị yaa Karaịs.”
English Translation: “Therefore let all Israel be assured of this: God has made this Jesus, whom you crucified, both Lord and Messiah.”

Transcript: Mgbe nde madụm nọrụ na ya ibom nụdụrụ ihe Pita kwuru, ya o metuwo na obu ọkam, wo sị Pita yaa ndeozi Karaịsịm woa ya yị, “Ụmụnna, ayị je-eme ẹgaa?”
English Translation: When the people heard this, they were cut to the heart and said to Peter and the other apostles, “Brothers, what shall we do?”

Transcript: Pita sị wo, “Unu chegerie, habue ihe ọjọọ uunu, na-emie onye ọọbụla na ime unu baụtizim, na ẹha Jisọs Karaịs ma Chineke gbaharị unu ihe ọjọọ uunu na ohu. Na unu anatakọ ya Maa Nsọa a nịrị.
English Translation: Peter replied, “Repent and be baptized, every one of you, in the name of Jesus Christ for the forgiveness of your sins. And you will receive the gift of the Holy Spirit.

Transcript: Ya nkwam Chineke kweri dịịrị unu, maa ụmụ uunu, maa ndem nọgarị na ibe otele, bụ nde Onyenwoayị bụ Chineke ka je-eku.”
English Translation: The promise is for you and your children and for all who are far off—for all whom the Lord our God will call.”

Transcript: Pita kwue ọtụtụ okwu dị iche iche weri sie wo ẹka na ntị, na-egoro wo sị, “Unu zọfụta onwuunu na ẹka ntaram-ahụhụa je-adakwasị nde ihe ọjọọ nke ụwaa.”
English Translation: With many other words he warned them; and he pleaded with them, “Save yourselves from this corrupt generation.”

Transcript: Ndem na ohu nabatarị ozie Pita ziri wo, e mie wo baụtizim. Ihe dịka nnụ madụ ẹsaa na ihu madụ iri (3,000) bụ nde e yekooru nde na-eso ụzọ Jisọs na ya izukum.
English Translation: Those who accepted his message were baptized, and about three thousand were added to their number that day.

Transcript: Nke wo dị nabataworuni, kweri na Jisọs jirim obu wo oohu na-eme ihe ndeozi Karaịs nọrụ na-ezi, na-enwo nzuko na etiti onwowo, na-eri oriri nsọ nke Onyenwoayị, na-ekpe ekpere.
English Translation: They devoted themselves to the apostles’ teaching and to fellowship, to the breaking of bread and to prayer.

Transcript: Otue ọrụ ahụma ya ọrụ-ebube ndeozi Karaịs nọrụ na-arụga kakọta nde madụ ẹnya.
English Translation: Everyone was filled with awe at the many wonders and signs performed by the apostles.

Transcript: Ndie na ohu nworu ntụkwasịobu na ibe Karaịs nọ bụkọtarị nnanị, ka ọọdị ịkpa oke dị na etiti wo na ihe wo nwoge.
English Translation: All the believers were together and had everything in common.

Transcript: Onye nwo ihe o nwo, na o rie ye na-eweri na-egbokote mkpa onye ọọbụla.
English Translation: They sold property and possessions to give to anyone who had need.

Transcript: Nke izuha na wo ana-ezukote na Oke Ulo Nsọ. Na-aga na ulo na ulo ndeke wo, jiri o
English Translation: Every day they continued to meet together in the temple courts. They broke bread in their homes and ate together with glad and sincere hearts,

Transcript: Mkpuhe Chineke nịrị Jisọs Karaịs ya o kpuheeri nde ụmụọrụ a, ihe aamagị atọnwa ike na ọ gbaa. Jisọs me amata a hite na iziteri nwaọrụ a Jọn maaozi e.
English Translation: The revelation from Jesus Christ, which God gave him to show his servants what must soon take place. He made it known by sending his angel to his servant John,

Transcript: Jọn na-agba ama ihe ọọbụla ọ hụrụ, nke bụ okwu Chineke yaa ama Jisọs Karaịs gbarị.
English Translation: who testifies to everything he saw—that is, the word of God and the testimony of Jesus Christ.

Transcript: Ngọzi dịịrị onye ọọbụla na-agụ okwu nke amụma a. Ngọzi na-adịrị ndem na-anụ anị, na-etiye obu na ihe e deri na ya, maka na ya mgbem agbanyabafuwo.
English Translation: Blessed is the one who reads aloud the words of this prophecy, and blessed are those who hear it and take to heart what is written in it, because the time is near.

Transcript: Ẹkwụkwọ Jọn deeri nde chọchị ẹsaa dị na Eshia. Na ẹwụọma yaa udo Chineke dịrị unu, bụ onyem nọnị, onyem nọrụnị, bụkwarị onyem ka je-abịa, maa nke hi na ẹka maa ẹsaam nọ na ihu oche ezie,
English Translation: John, To the seven churches in the province of Asia: Grace and peace to you from him who is, and who was, and who is to come, and from the seven spirits before his throne,

Transcript: maa nke hi na ẹka Jisọs Karaịs, onye ama kwesiri ntụkwasịobu, bụ ifufu mbụ nke hi na ọnwụ pavuru, bụkọ onye ọchịchị nke nde eze ụwaa na ohu. Onye hụrụ ayị na ẹnya weri mee ye nafụta ayị na ihe ọjọọ aayị.
English Translation: and from Jesus Christ, who is the faithful witness, the firstborn from the dead, and the ruler of the kings of the earth. To him who loves us and has freed us from our sins by his blood,

Transcript: Onye meri ayị nde ọchịchị yaa nde ọchụẹja Chinekie yaa Nnịa, onye otuto yaa ikike bụ nkie rue mgbe agwụ-agwụ! Amịn.
English Translation: and has made us to be a kingdom and priests to serve his God and Father—to him be glory and power for ever and ever! Amen.

Transcript: Le ẹnya, o ji ẹnwụrọkụ elugwe bịataje, madụ oohu je-ahụ a, maa ndem marị a arụa; madụ oohu na ụwa je-ada owu ẹkwa maka a. Ọ bụ nke o je-ọdị! Amịn.
English Translation: “Look, he is coming with the clouds,”and “every eye will see him, even those who pierced him”; and all peoples on earth “will mourn because of him.”So shall it be! Amen.

Transcript: “Ọ bụ m bụ Alụfa yaa Omega,” ọ bụ ihe Onyenwoayị Chineke kwuru, “Onye nọnị ẹɦụọdị, Onye nọrụnị na mbụ, Onye ka je-abịa, Onye bụ Ọkakaa.”
English Translation: “I am the Alpha and the Omega,” says the Lord God, “who is, and who was, and who is to come, the Almighty.”

Transcript: Mụoni bụ Jọn, nwanna uunu yaa onye unua ya yịkọ na ntaram[1]ahụhụ yaa ọchịchị isi yaa ndidi nke bụ okere aayị na ime Jisọs, nọrụ na alị Patịmọs mini gbarị gburugburu maka okwu Chineke yaa ọgbụgba ama nke eziokwu Jisọs kpuheri.
English Translation: I, John, your brother and companion in the suffering and kingdom and patient endurance that are ours in Jesus, was on the island of Patmos because of the word of God and the testimony of Jesus.

Transcript: Na ya izukum nke Onyenwoayị, Maa Nsọ weeri ọnọdụ na ime m, m nụ oke ụda olu darị ka ọ bụ ofuike na azụ m.
English Translation: On the Lord’s Day I was in the Spirit, and I heard behind me a loud voice like a trumpet,

Transcript: Ya ọ sị, “Gbaa ihe ọọbụla ị hụrụ na ẹkwụkwọ, zijeri e nde chọchị dị na isi obodo e ẹsaa: Efesọs, Sumẹna, Pẹgamọm, Tiyatira, Sadis, Filadẹlfia yaa Lawodisia.”
English Translation: which said: “Write on a scroll what you see and send it to the seven churches: to Ephesus, Smyrna, Pergamum, Thyatira, Sardis, Philadelphia and Laodicea.”

Transcript: M tụgarịa ma m hụ onye na-ekwuru m okwu, m hụ nguzobe oriọkụ ẹsaa e jiri ọlaodo kpụa.
English Translation: I turned around to see the voice that was speaking to me. And when I turned I saw seven golden lampstands,

Transcript: Na etiti ya nguzobe oriọkụmga, ya onwo onye dịka, “nwa nke madụ”, yeri uwe mwụda ruru e na agbọ ọkpa. E jiri ihe okike ọlaodo kebugie na obu.
English Translation: and among the lampstands was someone like a son of man, dressed in a robe reaching down to his feet and with a golden sash around his chest.

Transcript: Isie yaa ẹgbịsị dị a na isi na-acha zazaza ka ureze, ma ọ bụgụ ka Sunoo, ẹnya a na-eke poo ka ọkụ na-ere ere.
English Translation: The hair on his head was white like wool, as white as snow, and his eyes were like blazing fire.

Transcript: Ọkpa a na-ekpe sososo ka mkpụrụ igwe a gụfụtarị na ọkụ nde na-akpụ ụzụ, olu e na-adaa ka okpukpo mini gbajeje warawara.
English Translation: His feet were like bronze glowing in a furnace, and his voice was like the sound of rushing waters.

Transcript: Ọ chịm chichinda ẹsaa na ẹka ikengie, mma-aga ihu ẹbọọ dị nkọ hi e na ọnụ sofute. Ihu e na-acha ka mgbe ẹnyanwụ kakọta achakebe ike.
English Translation: In his right hand he held seven stars, and coming out of his mouth was a sharp, double-edged sword. His face was like the sun shining in all its brilliance.

Transcript: Na mgbe m hụrụ a, m daa na agịga ọkpa a ka onye nwụhụrụ anwụhụ. Ya o weri ẹka ikengie tụkwasị m sị, “Asọsị ụjọ! Ọ bụ m bụ Ibuzọ yaa Ikpeazụ.
English Translation: When I saw him, I fell at his feet as though dead. Then he placed his right hand on me and said: “Do not be afraid. I am the First and the Last.

Transcript: Ọ bụ m bụ ya Onyem dị ndụ, a nwụhụwaarị m anwụhụ, ọbụ ẹɦụọdị adị m ndụ rue mgbe agwụ-agwụ! Ọ bụkwanụ m ji ọgbọgọrọ ọnwụ yaa Hedis
English Translation: I am the Living One; I was dead, and now look, I am alive for ever and ever! And I hold the keys of death and Hades.

Transcript: “Gbaa ihie na ohu ị hụrụ, ihe dị ẹɦụọdị yaa ihe ka je-agba ma emedue.
English Translation: “Write, therefore, what you have seen, what is now and what will take place later.

Transcript: Ihe chichinda m ẹsaa ị hụrụ m na ẹka ikenge yaa ibe nguzobe oriọkụ ẹsaam fụtarị bụo: Ya chichindam ẹsaa bụ nde maaozi chọchịm ẹsaa, ta ya ibe nguzobe oriọkụm ẹsaa bụrụ ya chọchịm woa ẹsaa.”
English Translation: The mystery of the seven stars that you saw in my right hand and of the seven golden lampstands is this: The seven stars are the angels of the seven churches, and the seven lampstands are the seven churches.

Transcript: “Dejeri maaozi chọchị dị na Efesọs ẹkwụkwọ ozi, sị a, “Ihie bụ ozi onyem ji chichinda ẹsaa na ẹka ikenge, onyem na-eje ije na etiti ibe eguzobe oriọkụ ẹsaam e jiri ọlaodo kpụa.
English Translation: “To the angel of the church in Ephesus write: These are the words of him who holds the seven stars in his right hand and walks among the seven golden lampstands.

Transcript: Amaarị m ọrụ uunu; na unu arụsịwo ọrụ ike, nwoe ogologo ntachiobu. Amaarị m na unu ekpuchigi nde ihe ọjọọ, na unu eletegilewo ndem sị na wo bụ ndeozi Onyenwoayị mgbe ọọdịgị ihe wo bụ, unu chọfụta na wo bụ nde ụga.
English Translation: I know your deeds, your hard work and your perseverance. I know that you cannot tolerate wicked people, that you have tested those who claim to be apostles but are not, and have found them false.

Transcript: Unu enwoworu ndidi, taa ahụhụ maka ẹha m, ọbụ na unu aka asụgụ ngọngọ dakafụụ.
English Translation: You have persevered and have endured hardships for my name, and have not grown weary.

Transcript: Ọbụ na o nworu ihe aanị megideri unu: unu enwosigi ịhụnaẹnyam unu nworu na mgbe mbụ.
English Translation: Yet I hold this against you: You have forsaken the love you had at first.

Transcript: Unu rịgarịkwelie ogogo unu hi na ya bịa adaa! Unu chegerie ẹɦụọdị ha[1]bue ihe ọjọọ uunu galatachaa na ụzọm unu nọwaarị aga na mbụ. Ya ọ bụrụ na unu ajụka ehigi na ihe ọjọọ uunu fụta, eje m apanarị unu nguzobe oriọkụ uunu pafụụ na ibom a na-adọba a.
English Translation: Consider how far you have fallen! Repent and do the things you did at first. If you do not repent, I will come to you and remove your lampstand from its place.

Transcript: Ọbụ na o nworu ihe aanị unu nwo bụ ihe dị ma, unu ekwegi ihe nde otu Nịkọlas na-eme ẹɦụm mụoni aachọkọgụ ihe wo na-eme.
English Translation: But you have this in your favor: You hate the practices of the Nicolaitans, which I also hate.

Transcript: “Onye nwo ntị, ya ọ nụụ ihe Maa Nsọ na-ekwuru nde chọchị. Onye medue merie na mụ anị a ikike na o soru rie ihe hi na ya osisim na-anị ndụ dị na Paradaịsị Chineke.”
English Translation: Whoever has ears, let them hear what the Spirit says to the churches. To the one who is victorious, I will give the right to eat from the tree of life, which is in the paradise of God.

Transcript: “Dejeri maaozi nke chọchị dị na Sumẹna ẹkwụkwọ ozi, sị a, “Ihie bụ ihe onyem bụ mma[1]lite yaa ọgwụgwụ sị, onyem nwụhụdụrụnị ta dịkwakwa ndụ ọzọ.
English Translation: “To the angel of the church in Smyrna write: These are the words of him who is the First and the Last, who died and came to life again.

Transcript: Amaworu m na ọ dịgị nke ọ ha uunu, ta marị ihe na-adakwasị uunu, ọbụ[1]kwanụ na unu nwom ihe! Amaarị m nke ndem sị na wo bụ nde Juu aadịgị ihe wo bụ na-ekwuto unu; wo bụ nde otu ọgbakọ Ekwensu!
English Translation: I know your afflictions and your poverty—yet you are rich! I know about the slander of those who say they are Jews and are not, but are a synagogue of Satan.

Transcript: Unu asọkwa ihe ọọbụla je-adakwasị unu asọ. Unu gebechee ntị, Ekwensu je-anwagile ntụtụ na ime uunu, kpụrụ ụfọdị na ime uunu je-etiye na mkpọrọ, na unu ataa ahụhụ abalị iri. Unu nọgide na ikwesi ntụkwasịobu na ibe m nọ, ma ọ bụkọhaagị na a na-eye unu mma na nkọ[1]lọ, eje m eji ndụ kpube unu okpueze nke mmeri.
English Translation: Do not be afraid of what you are about to suffer. I tell you, the devil will put some of you in prison to test you, and you will suffer persecution for ten days. Be faithful, even to the point of death, and I will give you life as your victor’s crown.

Transcript: “Onye nwo ntị, ya ọ nụụ ihe Maa Nsọ na-akarị nde chọ[1]chị. Onye meririni, ọnwụ nke kwe ẹbọọ amagị emeru e ụhụ.”
