English Translation: Whoever has ears, let them hear what the Spirit says to the churches. The one who is victorious will not be hurt at all by the second death.

Transcript: “Dejeri maaozi nke chọchị dị na Pẹgamọm ẹkwụkwọ ozi, sị a, “Ihie bụ okwu hi na ọnụ onyem ji mma-aga ihu ẹbọọm dị nkọ.
English Translation: “To the angel of the church in Pergamum write: These are the words of him who has the sharp, double-edged sword.

Transcript: Amaarị m ibe unu bu, na ibom Ekwensu deberi oche ezie. Unu guzooru m na eziokwu, unu ahabudigi ntụkwasịobu unu nwo na ibe m nọ, ma ọ bụkọhaagị na mgbem e gburu onyem na-agbarị m ama a na-eku Antipas, na ibom Ekwensu bu.
English Translation: I know where you live—where Satan has his throne. Yet you remain true to my name. You did not renounce your faith in me, not even in the days of Antipas, my faithful witness, who was put to death in your city—where Satan lives.

Transcript: “Ọbụ na o nworu akpụrụ ihe ole m nworu megide unu. O nworu ntụtụ na ime uunu na[1]eso ozizi Balaam, onye Balak ziri na o wete ihe mkpọlụkọ dochie ụmụ Izirẹlụ ụzọ, meri woni wo je-erie ihe e jiri chụarị ẹrụsị ẹja, na-enwoko mmeko nwoke yaa nwanyị aabụgụ nde lụtaarị onwowo.
English Translation: Nevertheless, I have a few things against you: There are some among you who hold to the teaching of Balaam, who taught Balak to entice the Israelites to sin so that they ate food sacrificed to idols and committed sexual immorality.

Transcript: O nwokoru ntụtụ na ime uunu na-eso ozizi nde otu Nịkọlas.
English Translation: Likewise, you also have those who hold to the teaching of the Nicolaitans.

Transcript: Unu chegerie! Unu echegerigi, abịa[1]kwuteje mnwe unu hoohoo, je-eji okwu ọnụ m dịka mmaaga je-alụso ya ndem ọgụ.
English Translation: Repent therefore! Otherwise, I will soon come to you and will fight against them with the sword of my mouth.

Transcript: “Onye nwo ntị, ya ọ nụụ ihe Maa Nsọ na-ekwuru nde chọchị. Onye meririni, eje m anị a ya manam e zomiri ezomi. Eje m anịkọ a mkpume ọcha e deri ẹha ọɦụụ na elu e. Ọ bụnwa onyem natarị anị je-ama ihe e deri na elu e.”
English Translation: Whoever has ears, let them hear what the Spirit says to the churches. To the one who is victorious, I will give some of the hidden manna. I will also give that person a white stone with a new name written on it, known only to the one who receives it.

Transcript: “Dejeri maaozi nke chọchị dị na Tiyatira ẹkwụkwọ ozi, sị a, ihie bụ ozi Ọkpara Chineke, onye ẹnya a na-acha ka ọkụ na-ere ere, ọkpa a dịka igwe e hi na ụzụ gụ[1]fụta.
English Translation: “To the angel of the church in Thyatira write: These are the words of the Son of God, whose eyes are like blazing fire and whose feet are like burnished bronze.

Transcript: Amaarị m ihe unu na-eme, marị ịhụnẹnya yaa okwukwe uunu, marị ejem-ozi uunu yaa ogologo ntachiobu uunu. A makọọrụ m na unu na-emezu ihe ọọbụla karịa nke unu nọrụ na-eme na mbụ.
English Translation: I know your deeds, your love and faith, your service and perseverance, and that you are now doing more than you did at first.

Transcript: “Ọbụ na ọ ka o nwokweriri ihe m nwo megide unu. Unu na-anabata nwanyịm a na-ekuJezibẹl, onye na-eku onwoe onye-amụma. O na-ozilu ndeke m ihu ịba na inwo mmeko nwoke yaa nwanyị aabụgụ nde lụtaarị onwowo, na-eriko ihe e jiri chụarị ẹrụsị ẹja.
English Translation: Nevertheless, I have this against you: You tolerate that woman Jezebel, who calls herself a prophet. By her teaching she misleads my servants into sexual immorality and the eating of food sacrificed to idols.

Transcript: Anịwo mu e efe ihi na ihe ọjọọ ya fụta ọbụ na o kwegi ịkwụsị omume ihe ọjọọ ya.
English Translation: I have given her time to repent of her immorality, but she is unwilling.

Transcript: “Eje m je-alọba a na ugbo ntaram-ahụhụ. Ndem na ohu soko e na-eme ihe ọjọọ je-abayeko na ezibe ntaram-ahụhụ. Ọ bụkwam ma wo hi na ya ụzọ ọjọọ yam fụta, chegerie.
English Translation: So I will cast her on a bed of suffering, and I will make those who commit adultery with her suffer intensely, unless they repent of her ways.

Transcript: Eje m akụgbusitum ndem na ohu na-eso Jezibẹl, na nde chọchị na ohu amarị na ana m enyoche obu madụ oohu, na-akwụhachi onye ọọbụla ụgwọ dịka nke ọrụ a dị.
English Translation: I will strike her children dead. Then all the churches will know that I am he who searches hearts and minds, and I will repay each of you according to your deeds.

Transcript: “Ndem na ohu fọrụ na Tiyatira, ndem eesogu ozizi Jezibẹl, esoko[1]gu ihom ndekie na-eku ihe omimi nzuzo nke Ekwensu, ejegi m je-ebo unu ivu ẹrọ ọzọ.
English Translation: Now I say to the rest of you in Thyatira, to you who do not hold to her teaching and have not learned Satan’s so-called deep secrets, ‘I will not impose any other burden on you,

Transcript: Ọ bụnwa unu gidesie ihe unu ji ẹka ike tututu rue mgbe m je-abịa.
English Translation: except to hold on to what you have until I come.’

Transcript: “Onyem je-enwo mmeri, na-eme ihe m na-achọ tututu rue na isi, eje m anị a ikike ịchị mba na ohu.
English Translation: To the one who is victorious and does my will to the end, I will give authority over the nations—

Transcript: “O je-oji mkpara igwe na[1]achị wo, ọ je-ọjụwasị wo na alị ka ite e jiri ụrịa kpụa.
English Translation: that one ‘will rule them with an iron scepter and will dash them to pieces like pottery’ —just as I have received authority from my Father.

Transcript: “Eje m anị a ikike ẹɦụm Nna m nịrị m. Eje m anịkọ a chichinda ụtụtụ.
English Translation: I will also give that one the morning star.

Transcript: “Onye nwo ntị, ya ọ nụụ ihe Maa Nsọ na-ekwuru nde chọchị
English Translation: Whoever has ears, let them hear what the Spirit says to the churches.

Transcript: “Dejeri maaozi nke chọchị dị na Sadis ẹkwụkwọ ozi, sị a, “Ihie bụ okwu ya onyem ji Maa ẹsaam nke Chineke yaa chichinda ẹsaam. Amaarị m ọrụ uunu; nde a na-ahụta ka nde dị ndụ, ọbụ na unu nwụhụrụ anwụhụ.
English Translation: “To the angel of the church in Sardis write: These are the words of him who holds the seven spirits of God and the seven stars. I know your deeds; you have a reputation of being alive, but you are dead.

Transcript: Unu pavuru! Kwagide ihe fọdịịrị unu na-achọkọzukwenu anwụ[1]hụ, maka na-ahụtagị m ọrụ uunu ka ihe zuru oke na ihu Chineke m.
English Translation: Wake up! Strengthen what remains and is about to die, for I have found your deeds unfinished in the sight of my God.

Transcript: Unu rịta ihom e ziri unu, unu nụwokoru, unu rube isi chegerie. Ọbụ ya ọ bụrụ na unu apavuurugu, eje m ekwenwe gọdịm bịa na mberede ka onye ohi, ka unu aama mgbe m je-eji bịakwute unu.
English Translation: Remember, therefore, what you have received and heard; hold it fast, and repent. But if you do not wake up, I will come like a thief, and you will not know at what time I will come to you.

Transcript: “Ọbụ na unu ka enwom madụ ole-na-ole aaka emerugu uwe wo na Sadis. Mụa wo je-ayị jie njem, yeri uwe ọcha, maka na wo bụ nde zuru oke, kwesi ekwesi.
English Translation: Yet you have a few people in Sardis who have not soiled their clothes. They will walk with me, dressed in white, for they are worthy.

Transcript: Onye nworu mmeri je-esoko wo yeri ya uwe ọcham. A magị m akachafụ ẹha a na ẹkwụkwọ nke ndụ, kama eje m agba ama bayeri onye ọ bụ na ihu Nna m yaa nde maaozi e.
English Translation: The one who is victorious will, like them, be dressed in white. I will never blot out the name of that person from the book of life, but will acknowledge that name before my Father and his angels.

Transcript: Onye nwo ntị, ya ọ nụụ ihe Maa Nsọ na-ekwuru nde chọchị.”
English Translation: Whoever has ears, let them hear what the Spirit says to the churches.

Transcript: “Dejeri maaozi nke chọchị dị na Filadẹlfia ẹkwụkwọ ozi, sị a, “Ihie bụ okwu onyem dị nsọ, bụ eziokwu, onyem ji ya ire ọgbọgọrọm nke Devidi. Ihe ọ gụ ịgụ ha chi e. Ihe ọ gụ rị ọ dịgị onye nwo chikwe ru ike nuru ọ dịgị onye nworu ike ịgụha a.
English Translation: “To the angel of the church in Philadelphia write: These are the words of him who is holy and true, who holds the key of David. What he opens no one can shut, and what he shuts no one can open.

Transcript: Amaarị m ọrụ uunu. E meheworu m unu ọnụ-ụzọ na ihu uunu ọọdịgị onye nworu ike imechi e. Amaarị m na ikike uunu hanwa tịkọọ, ọbụ na unu edebewo okwu m, ka unu aagọnahị ẹha m.
English Translation: I know your deeds. See, I have placed before you an open door that no one can shut. I know that you have little strength, yet you have kept my word and have not denied my name.

Transcript: Ndem bụ nde otu nke ọgbakọ Ekwensu, sị na wo bụ nde Juu ibe ọọdịgị ihe wo bụ, eje m eme na wo bịa-adaa na alị na ihu uunu, kwete na a hụrụ m unu na ẹnya.
English Translation: I will make those who are of the synagogue of Satan, who claim to be Jews though they are not, but are liars—I will make them come and fall down at your feet and acknowledge that I have loved you.

Transcript: Ibe unu nworu ndidi debe ihe ọọbụla m tụrụ na iwu, eje m echebeko unu na mgbe ya oke ọnwụnwam je-abịakwasị ụmụ ụwa na ohu, ịnwagile madụ oohu bu na elụwa.
English Translation: Since you have kept my command to endure patiently, I will also keep you from the hour of trial that is going to come on the whole world to test the inhabitants of the earth.

Transcript: “Ụbịa m dịzunwe nso. Unu gidechee ihom unu ji, na ọ dịkwa onye je-anafụ unu okpueze uunu.
English Translation: I am coming soon. Hold on to what you have, so that no one will take your crown.

Transcript: Onye nworu mmeri bụ onye m je-eme na ọ bụrụ osisi ji ulo guzosi ike na ulo nsọ Chineke m. Onye ọ bụ amagị afụsị afụ na ulo nsọ Chineke m, na mụ edeye ẹha Chineke m, maa ẹha alị nsọ Chineke m na elu onye ọ bụ, yaa Jerusalẹm ọɦụụm Chineke m je-ehi na elugwe weride; na mụ edeyeko ya ẹha ọɦụụm mụ na elu onye ọ bụ.
English Translation: The one who is victorious I will make a pillar in the temple of my God. Never again will they leave it. I will write on them the name of my God and the name of the city of my God, the new Jerusalem, which is coming down out of heaven from my God; and I will also write on them my new name.

Transcript: Onye nwo ntị, ya ọ nụụ ihe Maa Nsọ na-ekwuru nde chọchị.”
English Translation: Whoever has ears, let them hear what the Spirit says to the churches.
